BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T220000
UID:260305_wCchTZCrUqwuq6z0Dd4Fw
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-13T19
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Empanadas: Sweet and Savory
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T200000
UID:260302mHG-hx1J_kuRFff7yRHtqg
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nFriday\, March 13\, 2026 5:00 PM – 8:00 PM\n\nEx
 perience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nBilingual\, Culinary Arts\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\
 n18 and older\n\n$100 – Registration Cost Master the art of empanada mak
 ing with both sweet and savory fillings. Learn dough techniques\, folding 
 methods\, and create delicious handheld pastries.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nD
 iscover the versatility of empanadas in this hands-on culinary class where
  you’ll master both sweet and savory variations of this beloved pastry. 
 Learn to create tender\, flaky dough from scratch and explore traditional 
 filling techniques that balance flavor and texture. You’ll prepare savor
 y empanadas with options like seasoned beef\, chicken\, cheese and vegetab
 les\, alongside sweet versions featuring fruit\, chocolate\, or dulce de l
 eche. Instruction covers proper dough handling\, folding and crimping tech
 niques for beautiful presentation\, and cooking methods including baking a
 nd frying. You’ll understand how to adjust moisture levels in fillings t
 o prevent soggy pastries and learn tips for making empanadas ahead for eas
 y entertaining. Whether you’re drawn to traditional Latin American recip
 es or creative fusion flavors\, this class gives you the skills to make pr
 ofessional-quality empanadas at home. Perfect for both beginners and exper
 ienced cooks looking to expand their pastry repertoire.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/empanadas-workshop/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
