BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Raven Gala 2026
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T220000
UID:260225Pu_NLXLaNE-DAH7rzGNMaA
DESCRIPTION:It’s that time of year! The Raven Gala 2026 is right around 
 the corner and it is the perfect opportunity to support a theater that br
 ings people together by nurturing young artists\, showcasing local talent\
 , and keeping the arts vibrant and accessible for our entire community. At
  a time when arts education and community spaces matter more than ever\, t
 he Raven continues to be a place where imagination thrives and everyone be
 longs.\n\nThe Raven’s Gala 2026 is a joyful celebration of the artists\,
  children\, educators\, and community who bring this theater to life. The 
 evening’s entertainment showcases the heart of the Raven\, with the **R
 aven Players**\, whose performances highlight the power of local storytell
 ing and community-driven theater. The celebration continues with **Young 
 at Heart Theatre**\, the Raven’s resident children’s program\, featuri
 ng talented young performers whose creativity\, confidence\, and joy onsta
 ge remind us why the arts matter.\n\nAdding to the magic are the students 
 from **St. John’s School\,** currently rehearsing Alice in Wonderland
  which performs on the Raven stage in March. Students from **The Heald
 sburg School** will also be performing musical numbers from past and upco
 ming productions. These young performers are the future of storytelling\, 
 imagination\, and creative expression.\n\nThe evening builds to a rousing 
 grand finale by nationally known recording artist **Pete Stringfellow**\,
  bringing the celebration to an unforgettable close. We even have a spec
 ial guest\, **Assemblyman Chris Rogers**\, who will be in attendance!\n\
 nFor those seeking the ultimate Raven Gala experience\, a limited number o
 f Platinum Tickets include an exclusive pre-show VIP event at The Taste of
  Tea featuring **Robert Goleman**\, whose dazzling performances have been
  described as “nothing short of astonishing.”\n\nYour support of the R
 aven’s Gala directly funds arts education\, youth programming\, and acce
 ss to the theater for local schools and nonprofit organizations. More than
  a venue\, the Raven is a gathering place\, and a living reminder that a s
 trong community is defined by its commitment to the arts. We cannot wait t
 o celebrate with you. \n\nDates: \n\nFriday\, March 13th.\n\nTime: \n\n
 7:13 PM\; Doors open 6:13 PM
LOCATION:The Raven Performing Arts Theater
URL:https://raventheater.org/events/raven-gala-2026/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
