END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
UID:260305mwJIK0vHbECX63FBlcq92Q
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-14T14
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FLAMENCO! LIVE! Saturday\, May 14th 2026 at The Big Easy Petaluma
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T200000
UID:260305ejyitppbx0qfYup2CvIIYg
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an intoxicating evening of fiery flamenco performa
 nces when FLAMENCO! LIVE! sets the stage on fire with the fury and passion
  of Spain's legendary Gypsies \\(Roma\\) with a Flamenco Dinner Show in th
 e intimate atmosphere of THE BIG EASY. EXPERIENCE flamenco as stirring dan
 ces\, blazing guitars\, and soulful singing will transport you to another 
 place and time. FEEL the HEAT...\n\nFLAMENCO! LIVE!\n\nSaturday\, March 14
 th 2026\n\nMelissa Cruz ~ Dancer BAOBOB Flamenco Dancers: Maria Soledad Sa
 nchez\, Kendra Pearson and Yumi Dews Pirouz "De Caspio" ~ Singer Roberto A
 guilar ~ Guitarist\n\nShowtime: 6 pm Doors: 5 pm $25 Pay at the Door Cash 
 or Card\n\nat The Big Easy Club and Restaurant 128 American Alley Petaluma
  USA\n\n\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*
 \\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\* Flamenco Shows e
 very other Month! The 2nd Saturday of the Month. Always different Artists.
  Always a different Show.\n\nFlamenco Dinner Show with delicious food and 
 a Full Bar are available\, not included in entrance fee.\n\nArrive early\,
  get a good table and enjoy the food! Line forms at 4:45 pm\n\n\\*Limited 
 Reservations available for parties of 5 - 6 or more. Call at: \\(707\\) 77
 4- 9072\n\n\\*Large fully ventilated restaurant\, plenty of room for spaci
 ng\, masks optional.\n\nFLAMENCO! LIVE! ﻿was envisioned\, conceived\, an
 d has thrived since 2002 in Sonoma County\, California\, now celebrating 2
 4 years! Presenting the collaborative efforts of the Bay Area's finest Fla
 menco Singers\, Guitarists and Dancers\, and supporting local Flamenco stu
 dents\, dreamers\, and talents\, our goal has been to present top-notch pe
 rformances. Phoebe Vernier "La Fibi" has brought decades of artistry and e
 nergy to the public of Sonoma County for the purpose of sharing the music\
 , song and dance\, the treasure of Southern Spain. Whether in the formal t
 heater or in a casual setting\, the respect\, purity\, and integrity of th
 is traditional\, yet living and evolving art form is always foremost.\n\nN
 ow in our 4rd Year of fiery Flamenco Shows!\n\n"Best Performing Dance Comp
 any" - The Northbay Bohemian's BEST of the Northbay!
LOCATION:The Big Easy
URL:https://flamencolive.weebly.com/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fruit Bats & Vetiver duo
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T000000
UID:260305T4WciXwUhEyXvVEeq5YAjg
DESCRIPTION:Hello from in here to all you out there.\n\nFruit Bats’ eigh
 th LP opens with this invocation\, this call from an isolated vocal room t
 o your headphones somewhere out in the world. It’s a beckoning for your 
 trust and attention\, but also an assurance in lonely times—a distillati
 on of melancholy wrapped in a danceable waltz.\n\n“The Pet Parade\,” t
 he title track to Fruit Bats’ newest album\, might be a surprising openi
 ng track for longtime fans of Eric D. Johnson’s beloved indie folk-rock 
 project.The six-and-a-half-minute tone poem smolders and drones over just 
 two chords\, inspired by the strange and silly community events that he sa
 w growing up outside of Chicago\, in La Grange\, Illinois\, in which peopl
 e dressed up and showed off their pets. Decades later\, The Pet Parade eme
 rges in troubled times\, living within what Johnson refers to as the beaut
 y and absurdity of existence.\n\nAt times upbeat and reassuring \\(“Eagl
 es Below Us”\\) and at times quietly contemplative \\(“On the Avalon S
 tairs”\\)\, The Pet Parade marks a milestone for Johnson\, who celebrate
 s 20 years of Fruit Bats in 2021. In some ways still a cult band\, in othe
 r ways a time-tested act\, Fruit Bats has consistently earned enough small
  victories to carve out a career in a notoriously fickle scene.
LOCATION:Dance Palace
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107705710?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
