BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Reclaim Your Calm A Harmonic Vagus Nerve Reset
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T150000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
UID:260214zlSdehP8N0ulGzNBKB1WzQ
DESCRIPTION:**Reclaim Your Calm: Sound\, Breath\, & Flow**\n\nJoin us for 
 a unique somatic experience that uses the hypnotic\, melodic resonance of 
 the Rav Vast drum to bathe your nervous system in healing frequencies. Unl
 ike traditional drumming\, the Rav Vast creates a “sound forest” of ov
 ertones that helps the mind settle and the body soften. In this session\, 
 we integrate: Vibrational Sound Bath: The ethereal tones of the Rav Vast t
 o lower your heart rate. Somatic Humming: To physically vibrate the vagus 
 nerve from the inside out\, syncing your breath with the drum. Flowing Qig
 ong: Gentle\, meditative movements to move “Qi” (energy) and release p
 hysical bracing in the body. Experience the shift from “survival mode”
  to “serenity.” Denise will guide you through: Qigong to open the body
 ’s energy channels. Humming to stimulate your internal “calm” switch
 . A Rav Vast Sound Bath to wash away tension with beautiful\, resonant har
 monics. Come home to your body. Leave feeling grounded\, peaceful\, and re
 newed.\n\n**About Denise Aubin\, MQT**\n\nDenise Aubin is a certified Medi
 cal Qigong Therapist (MQT) and the founder of Dance of Qigong. She discove
 red Qigong many years ago while traveling her own healing path and has a p
 assion for assisting others on their healing journey back to love. Qigong 
 is all about loving yourself and reconnecting with your joy. Denise loves 
 teaching and empowering others in this ancient art form of self healing ex
 ercises. Denise received her degree from the International Institute of Me
 dical Qigong and received certification as a Medical Qigong Therapist. Den
 ise has been a teacher and healer for over thirty years.
LOCATION:Energy Wave Center 
URL:https://energywavecenter.com/denise-aubin/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Aligning with Our Deepest Knowing: Wise View on the Path of Awaken
 ing
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T160000
UID:260214tzCZsb8ankKGXK1gHxb6_A
DESCRIPTION:with Dana DePalma\, MA\, MFT and Matthew Brensilver\, PhD\n\nT
 he Buddha says that wise view is the starting point—it is also the culmi
 nation of awakening. Yet\, delusion comes camouflaged as wisdom. What we 
 do not yet understand shapes our view and obscures freedom. What are the p
 rocesses by which we realize and align with our deepest knowing?\n\nTogeth
 er\, we’ll consider the various aspects of the Dharma path that help us 
 wake up to the assumptions that shape our experience and behavior: deep at
 tention\, spiritual friendship\, and surrendering to this moment. We’ll 
 reflect on what we’ve known in our clearest moments and what truly matte
 rs in how we relate to life. Together we’ll open to our embodied experie
 nce of wise view and how it supports meeting each moment with wisdom and l
 ove.\n\nDuring this day of practice\, we’ll offer guided and silent medi
 tation practice\, Dharma reflections\, and time for dialogue. All are welc
 ome.
LOCATION:Spirit Rock Meditation Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/aligning-with-our-deepe
 st-knowing-wise-view-on-the-path-of-awakening/18115051/2026-03-14T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
