DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
UID:260207XgX4UjNLd0CTHAJNsbKlnA
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to save a life!\n\nFocusing on recognizing and treat
 ing life-threatening situations in the critical minutes before 911 arrives
 \, we will cover adult and infant CPR\, AED use\, handling choking as well
  as what to do in cases of severe bleeding\, sudden illness\, heart attack
 \, stroke and more.\n\nFocusing on recognizing and treating life-threateni
 ng situations in the critical minutes before 911 arrives\, we will cover a
 dult and infant CPR\, AED use and handling choking\, as well as what to do
  in cases of severe bleeding\, sudden illness\, heart attack\, stroke and 
 more.\n\nWe'll be using modern manikins and equipment in a small-group set
 ting\, and answering questions along the way. Your American Red Cross cert
 ificate will be valid for 2 years.\n\n(This community class event is held 
 at a branch of Sonoma County Library. We thank them for their hospitality.
  They have requested that we mention that this program is neither sponsore
 d by nor affiliated with the Sonoma County Library. Done!)\n\nPlease get i
 n touch with any questions!\n\nCollapse description
LOCATION:Petaluma Library
URL:https://riverpreparedfirstaid.com/community-classes/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Italian Ricotta Favorites: Sweet and Savory Classics
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T140000
UID:260207QmHJx-kEdUO7EWA6HUVSwQ
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, March 14\, 2026 10:00 AM – 12:00 PM\n
 \nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nBilingual\, Culinary Arts\n\nAge\\(s\\
 )\n\n18 and older\n\n$100 – Registration CostExplore ricotta three ways 
 in this Italian cooking class. Make delicate gnudi\, whipped ricotta crost
 ini\, and traditional torta di ricotta romana.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nDisc
 over the incredible versatility of ricotta cheese in this hands-on Italian
  cooking class featuring three distinct preparations that showcase this be
 loved ingredient. You’ll learn techniques ranging from delicate pasta-ma
 king to elegant appetizers and classic Italian desserts. Start by creating
  pillowy ricotta gnudi\, those cloud-like dumplings that are lighter than 
 traditional gnocchi\, served with a vibrant tomato sauce. Master the art o
 f achieving the perfect texture and learn how to handle the delicate dough
  for consistently beautiful results. Next\, prepare whipped ricotta crosti
 ni topped with honey and fresh thyme\, an elegant appetizer that balances 
 creamy\, sweet\, and herbaceous flavors on crispy bread. Finally\, you’l
 l bake torta di ricotta romana\, a traditional Roman ricotta cake that’s
  subtly sweet and wonderfully moist. This classic dessert demonstrates how
  ricotta creates tender\, delicate baked goods with authentic Italian char
 acter. Throughout the class\, you’ll gain confidence working with fresh 
 ricotta\, understanding how its moisture content and handling affect each 
 dish differently. Whether you’re looking to expand your Italian cooking 
 repertoire or simply love ricotta\, this class provides techniques and rec
 ipes you’ll return to again and again. Perfect for intermediate home coo
 ks ready to explore authentic Italian preparations.Membership has its bene
 fits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above receive 10% off the registration 
 cost for any class purchase over $40. Materials fees are not discounted.\n
 \nBecome a member today and find community\, connection\, and creativity.\
 n\nLocation\n\nRoom 109\, Rotary Kitchen
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/italian-ricotta-favorites/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to Image Transfers
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T170000
UID:260207Jv3bTbcdaEaBmsQVGyMRZQ
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, March 14\, 2026 10:00 AM – 5:00 PM\n\
 nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nDrawing & Paint
 ing\, Printmaking\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$265 – Registration C
 ost $30 – Materials Fee $295 – Total Registration CostLearn photo tran
 sfer techniques onto canvas\, wood\, glass & paper in this hands-on worksh
 op with Bay Area artist Margot Hartford. Create unique art pieces!\n\nAbou
 t the Class\n\nJoin Bay Area guest artist Margot Hartford\, in this fun an
 d creative one-day workshop where students will explore a unique photo tra
 nsfer technique using personalized images. Learn how to effortlessly trans
 fer photos onto various surfaces\, including paper\, canvas\, glass and wo
 od. Margot will demonstrate this process using a printable clear acetate\,
  a specialized medium\, and acrylic paint. Students will be introduced to 
 the technique and will have the hands-on opportunity to create. The instru
 ctor will offer guided instruction in a supportive learning environment wi
 th a limited class size.\n\nWorkshop Requirements\n\nAfter registration\, 
 in advance of the workshop\, students will be required to email eight imag
 es to the instructor so they will be ready for use during the session. Eac
 h student will receive paper and wood panels to use as surfaces for transf
 erring their images. The class materials fee will include all the tools ne
 eded to create the project. Students will be able to take home all of thei
 r images and finished projects at the end of the workshop.\n\nAdditional N
 otice\n\nThis class requires hand dexterity to maneuver tools\, including 
 X-Acto blades\, and paintbrushes. The workshop includes six hours of instr
 uction with a short 30 minute lunch break.All Silver Memberships and above
  receive 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $40. Ma
 terials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find communi
 ty\, connection\, and creativity.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/introduction-to-image-trans
 fers/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
