BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hanging with Horses: Middle School
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T103000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T120000
UID:260305uamNHqcR70ijp4MVj2weQg
DESCRIPTION:A 4-week series of a screen-free space where middle schoolers 
 connect with horses\, feel supported\, and grow confidence.\n\nMiddle scho
 ol can be… a lot. Friendships changing. Siblings. Academic stress. Anxio
 us moments. Parents. You know. Horses are amazing friends\, guides\, liste
 ners\, and healers. They really know about relationships. AND they are exp
 erts at stress management. If you join Hanging with Horses\, you will hav
 e a blast and become a part of a wonderful herd \\(horses and humans.\\) Y
 ou might also...\n\nTry grounding and relaxation tools that actually help\
 n\nBuild confidence and leadership—just by being yourself\n\nLearn to sp
 eak horse while caring for the herd.\n\nYou don’t have to talk if you’
 re not ready. You don’t have to be “good with people.” You don’t n
 eed any horse experience.\n\nJust come as you are. The horses will meet yo
 u there 🐎✨\n\nThrough unpressured time “hanging with horses\,” gu
 ided group conversations\, and hands-on experiences\, participants will le
 arn to:\n\nUnderstand what stress and anxiety feel like in their own bodie
 s\n\nBuild healthier friendships and boundaries\n\nDevelop emotional aware
 ness and leadership skills\n\nPractice grounding and calming tools they ca
 n use anywhere\n\nGain confidence by tuning into themselves and their envi
 ronment\n\nHorses naturally reflect emotions and stress levels\, giving ki
 ds a powerful \\(and non-judgmental\\) way to learn about themselves and o
 thers.\n\n🐎NEIGH: Please come and check us out at an Open House for you
 th and parents: Speaking Horse ~ Year of the Fire Horse. \\(Free for Han
 ging with Horses families. Use the coupon code: MIDDLESCHOOL.\\) Register 
 here: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1981488694024?aff=oddtdtcreator\n\nScho
 larships are available. Please reach out or schedule a call to request- He
 artMindEquine@gmail.com\n\nWHAT THE 4 WEEKS INCLUDE\n\nEach session blends
  horse time \\+ group connection\, with flexibility to meet the needs of t
 he group. \\(Purchase once for the 4 week series.\\)\n\nParticipants will:
 \n\nGet to know one another and create a safe\, respectful group space\n\n
 Explore friendship dynamics\, social pressure\, and anxiety \\(including s
 ocial media stress\\)\n\nKids are encouraged \\(but not pressured\\) to st
 ep slightly outside their comfort zones while always honoring their bounda
 ries.\n\nWHO THIS GROUP IS FOR\n\nThis group is ideal for middle schoolers
  who:\n\nFeel stressed\, anxious\, lonely\, or overwhelmed\n\nStruggle wit
 h friendships or social dynamics\n\nWant to build confidence and leadershi
 p skills\n\nFOR THE PARENTS\n\nMiddle school can be a stressful and emotio
 nally intense time. This 4-week equine-assisted services group offers a su
 pportive\, screen-free environment where kids can slow down\, build confid
 ence\, and learn healthy ways to manage stress and anxiety.
LOCATION:Heart & Mind Equine Horse Rescue
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/hanging-with-horses-middle-school-tickets
 -1982833131272?aff=oddtdtcreator
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T170000
UID:260305J4PrWvDF2EeYnxSaU6pwyw
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-15T14
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
