BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sunday Sessions with "Fire Up!"
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T180000
UID:260227GLazkca1tEyouq_cC3Ld-w
DESCRIPTION:Griffo is excited to welcome Fire Up!\, a Bay Area Tribute to 
 the Garcia Saunders Songbook. This rotating cast of players will have you 
 transported with the first tune. Bodega Market Deli will be serving up foo
 d all day while the Griffo crew serves up delicious cocktails from our eve
 r rotating menu! Don't miss this homage to an era of music that never goes
  out of style!\n\nSee you Sundays!\n\nWho's Playing: Fire Up!\n\nWho's Coo
 king: Bodega Market Deli\n\nWhen: Sunday\, March 15th - Doors @ 1 pm\n\nWh
 ere: Griffo Distillery\n\nPlease RSVP for this FREE\, All Ages Event. Spac
 e is Limited.\n\nAbout the Band:\n\nFire up! Is a tribute band interpretin
 g the Jerry Garcia “Legion of Mary” era. Fire Up! is branded as “Son
 gs from the Garcia – Saunders songbook."\n\nFor note\, Fire Up! is a nam
 e of a Garcia Saunders studio album\, https://open.spotify.com/album/2b85g
 bWiMbAg3cvSUTMIBp\n\nOur project is funky\, bluesy\, Jamy\, RnB\, and Jazz
 y with an emphasis on the Hammond organ. One might say “Ballroom brawlin
 g\, baby making music" modeled after the 1972 – 1975 Legion of Mary era.
  It is different than what you hear from other JGB bands who focus on more
  of the 80’s and 90’s gospel Jerry era.
LOCATION:Griffo Distillery
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1469435291544648/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Glass Menagerie
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T160000
UID:2602271U6k_ohjQk-ZOHmCTJ24sQ
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Season at Curtain Call Theatre starts off with The Gl
 ass Menagerie\, the play that made Tennessee Williams famous.\n\nHave You 
 Ever Felt Stuck Between Your Dreams and Reality? This Play Gets It.\n\nIma
 gine being trapped in a tiny apartment during the Great Depression — no 
 money\, no way out\, just a family clinging to hopes that may never come t
 rue. That's exactly what The Glass Menagerie is about.\n\nWritten by Tenne
 ssee Williams — one of America's greatest playwrights — this story fol
 lows a restless son\, an overbearing mom\, and a painfully shy daughter as
  they each chase dreams that feel just out of reach. It's emotional\, poet
 ic\, and honestly… kind of hits different when you think about your own 
 life.\n\nThis iconic play is literally studied in classrooms worldwide\, s
 o seeing it live is like watching your textbook come to life — except wa
 y more powerful.\n\n📅 March 13–29\, 2026\n\n📍 20347 Hwy 116\, Mont
 e Rio\, CA\n\n🎟️ Grab your tickets at russianriverhall.com or call \\
 (707\\) 387-5072\n\nThe Glass Menagerie by Tennessee Williams is directed 
 by Michael Tabib.\n\nShowing at the Russian River Hall in Monte Rio\, CA f
 rom March 13-29\, 2026.\n\nProgram was made possible\, in part\, with fund
 s from Creative Sonoma and the California Arts Council \\(CAC\\).\n\nBy sp
 ecial arrangement with Dramatists Play Services\, Inc.
LOCATION:Curtain Call Theatre
URL:https://www.russianriverhall.com/2026/02/18/march-13-29-the-glass-mena
 gerie/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma Mushroom Foraging
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T140000
UID:260226sYcQgO46O0igu1yJiRq4Og
DESCRIPTION:These guided mushroom walks are about 2.5 hours north of San F
 rancisco in Sonoma.  All details you need\, including packing list\, meet
 -up location\, and more will be sent once your booking is confirmed.  Thi
 s is a wonderful weekend adventure to do alone or with friends and family.
  \n\n**What You'll Learn**\n\nThis experiential\, hands-on half-day progr
 am is all about the fascinating world of fungi and begins at 10:00 am. Le
 arning to forage for mushrooms is an ongoing life path. This program will 
 teach you foundational skills to be able to go out foraging on your own. 
 We will cover mushroom anatomy for identification\, symbiotic tree and pla
 nt relationships\, poisonous and edible mushrooms\, and forest safety.  T
 his winter\, it will be possible to find edibles such as porcini\, chanter
 elle\, yellowfoot\, black trumpet\, hedgehog\, and more.  The program als
 o includes community building\, mindful movement\, a cooking demo\, and a 
 tasting at the end.
LOCATION:Sonoma Coast
URL:https://www.forkinthepath.org/schedule/mushroom-foraging-sonoma-2025-l
 c6g9-shkzj-99aa8
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Look\, Listen and Bird!
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T113000
UID:260226n2kVIAn2Q0eWlIijY9kyXg
DESCRIPTION:We will focus \\(pun intended\\) on learning stories a
 nd field characteristics of local and migrating birds in the var
 iety of Sugarloaf habitats\, with an emphasis on ear birding. We
 ’ll discuss identification\, migration\, adaptations and our impo
 rtant role in improving habitat for birds. Let’s try to observ
 e at least 20 species!\n\nMeet at the White Barn parking lot. T
 ickets are $10 for general admission\, $5 for youth \\(12-17 yea
 r olds\; all minors must be accompanied by a parent or legal g
 uardian\\)\, students\, Sugarloaf members\, Sugarloaf or RFO volunt
 eers\, and free for children under 12. Wear layers\, appropriate
  footwear for muddy and/or slippery trails\, bring at least a q
 uart of water\, sun protection\, and if desired\, a snack. Binoc
 ulars are optional but welcome. Rain cancels. Parking fees apply.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/look-listen-and-bird/18
 226708/2026-03-15T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Eileen Ivers: Universal Roots
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T150000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T150000
UID:260225u7i1kyQOR0SxKJD49pQENQ
DESCRIPTION:**Eileen Ivers will change the way you think about the violin.
 **\n\nGroundbreaking musical star of Riverdance\, Grammy-winning and Emmy-
 nominated\, Eileen Ivers continues to push traditional fiddling boundaries
  from a folk music staple to a fiercely fresh\, powerfully beautiful\, int
 ensely driving world stage experience. Over a career spanning more than 40
  years\, she has performed and/or toured with such diverse artists as Stin
 g\, Patti Smith\, Al Di Meola\, Hall and Oates and The Chieftains and has 
 guest-starred with the London Symphony Orchestra\, Boston Pops\, over 60 s
 ymphony orchestras to date. \n\n**Sunday\, March 15th. 3:00 PM. Doors ope
 n at 2:00 PM.**
LOCATION:The Raven Performing Arts Theater
URL:https://raventheater.org/events/eileen-ivers-universal-roots/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Group Healing Circles Ceremony/Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T150000
UID:260225_gIqQYaVZUaRbthreKNhvQ
DESCRIPTION:This is an experiential intimate workshop arranged in two circ
 les of 7 participants\, designed to promote individual and group healing o
 n physical\, mental\, emotional and spiritual levels.\n\nIt is a guided in
 teractive process\, in which each participant will experience a variety of
  techniques using light\, sound\, touch\, energy and ancient wisdom healin
 g techniques. The goal of this ceremony is to help each person come into a
  place of inner balance and alignment. Circles and groups will be changed 
 approximately every 30-40 minutes allowing those in the center and the out
 er circles to receive the Gift of Creation.\n\n“The concept of simultane
 ous wheels of group healing was awesome to observe and participate with. 
  To observe Dr. Maria float from one circle to another identifying specifi
 c notes/frequencies given to her by Spirits for each specific person was a
 mazing. She also instructed people to aim certain colors to certain organs
 \, to allow for deeper healing to happen. The releases\, relief and raisin
 g of individual vibrations was absolutely amazing.”\n\nWhat makes this e
 vent especially powerful is that it takes place within the amplified bioen
 ergetic field of the EESystem. As Dr. Maria speaks about cellular resonanc
 e\, coherence\, and restoring balance\, guests will simultaneously be imme
 rsed in a scalar-energy environment designed to support optimal cellular c
 ommunication and energetic harmony. Whether you are new to her work or alr
 eady familiar with energy-based healing\, this is an invitation to explore
  what becomes possible when wisdom\, frequency\, and intention align. We l
 ook forward to welcoming you into the field.\n\nAbout Dr Maria Michael\n\n
 Dr. Maria D. Michael is a world renowned and respected medical intuitive\,
  channel\, empath\, healer\, psychic and teacher for over 40 years. She ha
 s been awarded 5 advanced degrees \\(all Summa Cum Laude\\)\, including a 
 Ph.D. in Counseling Psychology. She has doctorate-level training in Neurop
 sychology and Special Education and extensive post-doctoral studies in Psy
 choanalysis and Jungian Psychology. Additionally\, Dr. Michael is trained 
 and experienced in EMDR\, Hypnotherapy\, LENS Neurofeedback\, Neurolinguis
 tic Programming\, Eriksonian Hypnosis Training. She is a Lakota/Diné \\(N
 avajo\\) Traditional elder\, has participated in and led traditional Nativ
 e ceremonies and doctored alongside Lakota Medicine people. She has been s
 ought out worldwide for her powerful Medicine Energies and Healing abiliti
 es. Learn more about Dr Maria Michael at: https://drmariamichael.com/\n\nB
 ELIEFS\n\nDr. Maria Michael believes that we all come from the same Creati
 on\, and that everyone has the potential and capacity to communicate with 
 Creation. While the Lakota call Creation “The Great Mystery\,” other t
 raditions may refer to Creation\, with names such as\, “God\,” “the 
 Universe\,” “Allah\,” “Yahweh\,” “Divine Love\,” “Universa
 l Love” or “Cosmic Consciousness.”\n\nWe not only choose our human f
 amilies\, but also we choose\, initially at least\, our own unique form or
  tradition of understanding and communication with the Great Mystery. No f
 orm or tradition is better than another. Humans are merely attempting to u
 nderstand “That” which is beyond comprehension.\n\nAll messages from t
 he Great Mystery are compassionate and loving\, even though at times these
  messages may appear difficult. Creation’s message appears to us in what
 ever way we choose to comprehend it. Sometimes\, we are only capable of co
 mprehending deeply sensitive messages that resound in our hearts\, and som
 etimes only strong and “seemingly” shocking messages penetrate our def
 enses. This loving Spirit guides us to remove those obstacles that stand i
 n our way of becoming all that Creation and We intended us to be.
LOCATION:Energy Wave Center
URL:https://energywavecenter.com/gift-of-creation/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Festival Napa Valley Presents Solo Violinist Nancy Zhou
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T143000
UID:260225C7r1SUJWo0ysl133xgpddw
DESCRIPTION:Festival Napa Valley presents an intimate afternoon of solo
  violin at The Duckhorn Collection at Paraduxx. Set against the vineyard
 ’s iconic surroundings\, internationally acclaimed violinist Nancy Zhou
  offers a unique program spanning Baroque elegance to modern virtuosity\,
  revealing the full expressive power of the instrument. \n\nThe afternoon
  includes a reception featuring wines from The Duckhorn Collection\, as we
