DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T180000
UID:260213axN9WsccbEmTvQI_IMfKdg
DESCRIPTION:Jerry Hannan is a Marin-based singer/songwriter who has been p
 erforming regionally for years. Previously with the "Mad Hannans" Band\, a
 nd now as a solo artist or with a cadre of musicians as the Jerry Hannan B
 and. UUP's own Tony Blake will be drumming with the band\, along with two 
 other friends (guitar/banjo/dobro and bass). Jerry received notoriety for 
 his song "Society" that he wrote with Eddie Vedder (Pearl Jam) for the mov
 ie "Into the Wild."\n\nAmy Hogan is a beloved local singer-songwriter\, fr
 equently performing with members of her family. She performed in an earlie
 r UUP concert series\, and we are so happy to welcome her back!\n\nHeld in
  the sanctuary of this historic 1901 downtown Petaluma church\, the Sanctu
 ary Concert Series offers an acoustically excellent space for a listening 
 audience.\n\nDonation: $20\, with all proceeds going to the artists. An ad
 ditional donation opportunity to support the Sanctuary Coalition of Sonoma
  County will be available\, and all refreshment sales will benefit the org
 anization working to protect our migrant neighbors from abduction and depo
 rtation.
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalists of Petaluma
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/915472667673294/
