UID:260312zzhnM2bo4EqpDYVXHGyI_w
DESCRIPTION:Tiny Hooves\, Big Hearts: Our Ongoing Rescue Mission\n\nAt Goa
 tlandia\, our mission is simple: to give love\, safety\, and a second chan
 ce to animals who need it most.\n\nWe were recently called to rescue three
  baby goats. These tiny babies are now safe at Goatlandia\, and they need 
 bottle feeding several times a day to stay healthy and thrive.\n\nThat’s
  Where You Come In: The Bottle Baby Breakfast Club\n\nStarting March 6th\,
  join us for a heartwarming hour on the farm\, bottle-feeding and cuddling
  our newest rescues while supporting their care.\n\nYour $250 donation \\(
 covers milk and supplies for weeks of feedings\\) includes admission for u
 p to four guests for a private\, unforgettable visit to Goatlandia.\n\nCom
 e share the love\, feel the magic\, and help us give these little ones the
  future they deserve.
LOCATION:Goatlandia
URL:https://www.goatlandia.org/bottle-babies-breakfast-club
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma’s Female Culinary Voices Come Together for She’s All Th
 at Dinner
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T203000
UID:260310qDX88mjfP0SudQyocaBrqg
DESCRIPTION:On **Monday\, March 16**\, three of Sonoma County's most excit
 ing female culinary voices will come together for a *one-night-only* ***
 ‘She’s All That’ collaboration dinner in honor of International Wome
 n's Month***: Co-Owner & Chef Melissa McGaughey (Yanc) of **Quail & Condor
 **\, Co-Executive Chef Juliana Thorpe of **The Lodge at Dawn Ranch** and S
 arah Citron\, CEO and Co-Founder of **Bricoleur Vineyards**. \n\nSet amon
 g Guerneville’s ancient redwoods\, The Lodge at Dawn Ranch will welcome 
 Quail & Condor into its kitchen for an intimate evening of collaboration. 
 Chef Melissa will weave her Turkish heritage and acclaimed pastry expertis
 e into Chef Juliana’s South American-influenced California cooking acros
 s a four-course menu\, each course thoughtfully paired with wines from Bri
 coleur Vineyards\, poured by Sarah herself.\n\n**A portion of proceeds fro
 m ‘She’s All That’ will benefit the V Foundation for breast cancer r
 esearch**\, a mission especially close to the team’s heart. Since her ow
 n personal diagnosis two years ago\, Sarah and her Bricoleur team have rai
 sed more than $100\,000 for the cause.
LOCATION:The Lodge at Dawn Ranch
URL:https://www.opentable.com/booking/experiences-availability?rid=112036&
 restref=112036&experienceId=669754&utm_source=external&utm_medium=referral
 &utm_campaign=shared
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
