BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Walker Roaders
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260317T000000
UID:260224bq11yntNQU6yJzWk0HcD4A
DESCRIPTION:Scrotumtightening sea shanties. Great ballads of fire.\n\nThe 
 Walker Roaders is a collective of musicians steeped in what has become kno
 wn as ‘celtic-punk’. As both renowned originators and practitioners of
  the genre\, the supergroup\, as it has been described\, consists of James
  Fearnley co-founder of The Pogues on accordion\, Ted Hutt co-founder of F
 logging Molly on acoustic guitar\, and Marc Orrell multi-instrumentalist w
 ith Dropkick Murphys on banjo and mandolin. completing the line-up are sto
 ried producer Brad Wood on bass and coveted drummer Bryan Head.\n\n Named 
 after a street gang from Fearnley’s childhood in Manchester England\, th
 e two U.K. expatriates James and Ted formed the group in the U.S. with bos
 ton-raised Marc\, with whom James had formed a friendship when Dropkick Mu
 rphys supported The Pogues on their 2005 Christmas tour. The Walker Roader
 s released their first album in late 2019 a month or two before the bucket
  of the pandemic doused their plans \\(and those of bands everywhere\\) fo
 r a couple of years. The band is currently writing and recording their sec
 ond album\, for release in 2024. their first single from it – “There M
 ust Be Less To Life Than This” – was released in January 2024.
LOCATION:Little Saint
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107871083?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
