SUMMARY:The Art Of Acrylics
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T120000
UID:260210N0ZNn-Edv0mKa9uloT3xqQ
DESCRIPTION:Suzanne will demonstrate each week as students follow along wi
 th weekly painting projects\, exploring techniques such as layering thick 
 and thin paint\, using gels and palette knife\, and applying color theorie
 s. Students can work on their own projects as well. Whether you're a begin
 ner or looking to refine your skills\, this class covers everything you ne
 ed to know. You'll get informed instruction on how to begin a piece\, from
  choosing the right materials to selecting the perfect color palette. We'l
 l dive into composition techniques to help you craft a balanced\, captivat
 ing piece\, and walk you through the finishing touches that bring your wor
 k to life. Suzanne's artwork ranges from portraits\, figurative genre\, la
 ndscapes and caricatures. She has exhibited in juried shows including The 
 Society of Illustrators in New York and for 10 years at the Southern Calif
 ornia Laguna Beach Art Festival. She has taught classes and workshops for 
 many years and led lecture-demos at art associations from California to Wa
 shington State. For enrollment and supply list\, please text or call Suzan
 ne Carson at 707 888 2083
LOCATION:Datoire Foundation
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/the-art-of-acrylics/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Maija Peeples-Bright: Life is Just a Bowl of Terriers
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260318T170000
UID:260206DWGPVPoTlkGywPUkGAMa-w
DESCRIPTION:Maija Peeples-Bright is one of the few women artists associate
 d with Northern California's Funk Art movement of the late 1960s and '70s.
  Peeples-Bright's wildly inventive practice comprises robust compositions 
 bustling with animals of all kinds-her "beasties" as she calls them-formin
 g surreal\, imaginative landscapes in audacious impasto. Her zoological ar
 rangements represent alternate realities\, infusing exuberance and a sense
  of the absurd into impossible scenarios. Highly distinctive\, her textura
 l creature patterns revel in the extreme\, often taking up every inch of t
 he canvas\, multiplying her beasties into dizzying arrangements. Peeples-B
 right invites us into a decadence-gone-wild world all her own. The exhibit
 ion will feature a retrospective look at Peeples-Bright's career\, from he
 r early days of the Funk Movement to today.
LOCATION:Sonoma Valley Museum of Art
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/maija-peeples-bright-life-is-just-a-b
 owl-of-terriers/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
