BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T180000
UID:26021799b3weNK8UyO7eSLNUZv-A
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\nMARCH EXHIBIT: CELEBR
 ATING WOMEN\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\nRECEPTI
 ON: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists and ce
 lebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a 
 beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSono
 ma County artist\, Tosya Shore\, presents Celebrating Women\, paintings th
 at commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. Shore’s waterc
 olor works capture women in their element\, showing the multiple facets of
  their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with strong shapes and 
 interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways.  A la Degas\,
  we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Point.”  The arti
 st takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” where dominant trunk
  shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene.    “Just Bac
 k from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as the woman in quest
 ion catches her breath.  “There’s such special feeling in these every
 day moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – women deserve noth
 ing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore will be hosting the
  Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks
  Showcase features Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein Air\, a collection
  unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to France.  Roaming the 
 streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffer captured iconic sc
 enes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catches a true cultural v
 ibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored hangout for espresso 
 and conversation.  One is awed by the structure rising from the ground-le
 vel trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel Tower in “Paris is f
 or Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris – I hope through th
 ese plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of being there”\, stat
 ed Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Str
 eet\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 p
 m.    www.upstairsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact:
  Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Crochet for Beginners and Beyond
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260319T200000
UID:260214Wpd95ex6pUWGhlvv039E7Q
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nTuesdays\, March 3 – 24\, 2026 6:00 PM – 8:00 
 PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 201\, Fiber Arts Studio\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll 
 Levels\n\nFiber Arts\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$80 – Registration
  CostLearn to crochet or expand your skills in four relaxed Tuesday evenin
 g sessions. Beginners master foundational stitches\; experienced crafters 
 get project guidance.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nHave you always wanted to lear
 n to crochet – or are you ready to build on the skills you already have?
  Join us in the Fiber Arts Studio for four relaxed Tuesday evening session
 s dedicated to learning and practicing crochet. Beginners will start with 
 the essentials: how to hold the hook comfortably\, maintain even tension\,
  and work the foundational stitches – chain\, single crochet\, and doubl
 e crochet. Students with prior experience are welcome to begin a new proje
 ct or bring a work-in-progress for guidance and skill-building. All materi
 als are provided for beginners. Returning or experienced crocheters may br
 ing their own supplies or use yarn available in the studio.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
