BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bell Brothers
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T000000
UID:26022433rm-EA4PEG1wvI3NvV5TQ
DESCRIPTION:Meet The Bell Brothers\, a dynamic duo whose harmonies and son
 gwriting prowess have resonated with audiences for nearly two decades. Com
 prised of brothers Russ and Scott\, this powerhouse team has etched their 
 mark on the musical landscape with a fusion of Country\, Rock\, and Americ
 ana\, delivering a sound steeped in passion\, musicianship\, and gritty au
 thenticity.\n\nFor nearly 20 years\, The Bell Brothers have honed their cr
 aft\, evolving their sound while staying true to their roots. From intimat
 e coffee shops to electrifying stadiums\, their live shows are a testament
  to their commitment to delivering authentic performances that leave audie
 nces captivated.\n\nWhether they're crooning heartfelt country ballads or 
 belting out anthemic rock tunes\, The Bell Brothers' music speaks to the s
 oul\, forging a deep connection with listeners wherever they go. With each
  strum of the guitar and each note sung in harmony\, they continue to leav
 e an indelible mark on the hearts of fans old and new alike.
LOCATION:Santa Angelina Ranch
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107394819?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pi Jacobs
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T000000
UID:2602241u83-ZnNI06WUunzN0JnPQ
DESCRIPTION:Pi's new album\, Soldier On debuted at \\#44 on the AMA CHarts
 \, and spent over 16 weeks in the top 100.\n\nPi Jacobs draws inspiration 
 from her unconventional upbringing in “The Land of Weed and Wine” aka 
 Northern California. Blending roots-rock swagger and storytelling soul\, h
 er music has drawn comparisons to Tom Waits\, Dolly Parton\, and Lucinda W
 illiams. She has been heard on NPR\, DittyTV\, Austin Music TV\, Americana
  Highways\, American Songwriter Magazine\, and regularly on radio stations
  around the globe.\n\nPress:\n\n“…an explosive strength. Think a mix o
 f Melissa Etheridge\, Beth Hart\, and Wynonna Judd.” Glide Magazine\n\n
 “…roots-rock swagger and storytelling soul” -Top40 Charts\n\n“funn
 y\, poignant\, irreverent\, but always personal. Come enjoy her rootsy sou
 nd\, powerful vocals\, and charismatic stage swagger!  She might not heal 
 you\, but you'll forget your problems for a few hours” New Times San Lui
 s Obispo\n\n “…one of the most lyrically progressive and entertaining 
 songwriters of this era. "The ease and wisdom of greats like Dolly Parton 
 and Kris Kristofferson\, she belongs in their company.” Rock and Blues M
 use Rock and Blues Muse\n\n“Pi Jacobs has a voice that lets you in\, ‘
 sultry\,’ to be sure\, but it’s more than that…. Jacobs pulls togeth
 er one of the most difficult moves in music — she makes her own noise”
  - Claremont Courier\n\n“To say it’s all mesmerizing is an understatem
 ent… a songwriting gift like few other young artists have now.” – Be
 ntley’s Bandstand\n\n"Jacobs creates vivid images on par with masters li
 ke Tom Waits" Americana Highways\n\n"..a sultry\, feminine\, outlaw kind o
 f sound" American Songwriter\n\n“nothing here that doesn't impress at ev
 ery turn. Hot. This'll do to you what Lucinda's white album did to you.”
  Midwest Record\n\n"Divorce…whiskey…legal problems…cheaters…lies. 
 Whatever story comes next\, it's going to be a good one.” Twangville\n\n
 “great country music right here in LA” KCSN 88.5 Los Angeles
LOCATION:The Washoe House
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107909860?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Oakmont Meets Imagination - 52 Years of Creativity
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T160000
UID:260218F49dH_K3yUyXFYEKFEdsXQ
DESCRIPTION:This year’s show will feature the work of more than 50 membe
 rs of the Oakmont Art Association\, showcasing a rich and diverse collecti
 on of fine art. Visitors can expect to see original works in acrylic\, oil
 \, pastel\, watercolor\, fiber art\, and photography\, many of which will 
 be available for purchase. The exhibition highlights the wide range of sty
 les\, techniques\, and personal visions represented by Oakmont’s artists
 \, making each year’s show a fresh and inspiring experience.\n\nIn addit
 ion to fine art\, the show will include a lively Artisan Marketplace. Arti
 sans will offer an array of handcrafted items\, including jewelry\, photog
 raphy\, assemblage art\, fiber and fabric pieces\, original books\, potter
 y\, fused glass\, and many other unique small works. These one-of-a-kind c
 reations make perfect gifts and provide an opportunity to support local ar
 tists directly.\n\nThe event is designed to be both engaging and festive. 
 Attendees can enjoy live music by Oakmont musicians and appetizers while b
 rowsing the exhibits and visiting with artists. A popular highlight of the
  show is the annual raffle\, which adds an extra element of excitement whi
 le supporting a meaningful cause. In 2025 more than 50 raffle prizes were 
 generously donated by local businesses.  Raffle drawing and wine receptio
 n occurs at 3:30 p.m. Saturday.\n\nProceeds from the raffle benefit Art Qu
 est\, an organization that supports Santa Rosa students who are pursuing e
 ducation and careers in the arts. The generosity of past attendees has mad
 e a real impact—the 2025 raffle raised $3\,200 for Art Quest\, helping t
 o foster creativity and opportunity for young artists in our region.\n\nTh
 e Oakmont Art Association invites the community to attend this special eve
 nt\, celebrate 52 years of creativity\, and experience the imagination\, s
 kill\, and passion of its artists.
LOCATION:Berger Center
URL:http://oakmontart.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T180000
UID:260217eXEYBTH3FUCTHktrLHbTaA
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\nMARCH EXHIBIT: CELEBR
 ATING WOMEN\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\nRECEPTI
 ON: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists and ce
 lebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a 
 beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSono
 ma County artist\, Tosya Shore\, presents Celebrating Women\, paintings th
 at commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. Shore’s waterc
 olor works capture women in their element\, showing the multiple facets of
  their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with strong shapes and 
 interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways.  A la Degas\,
  we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Point.”  The arti
 st takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” where dominant trunk
  shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene.    “Just Bac
 k from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as the woman in quest
 ion catches her breath.  “There’s such special feeling in these every
 day moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – women deserve noth
 ing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore will be hosting the
  Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks
  Showcase features Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein Air\, a collection
  unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to France.  Roaming the 
 streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffer captured iconic sc
 enes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catches a true cultural v
 ibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored hangout for espresso 
 and conversation.  One is awed by the structure rising from the ground-le
 vel trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel Tower in “Paris is f
 or Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris – I hope through th
 ese plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of being there”\, stat
 ed Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Str
 eet\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 p
 m.    www.upstairsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact:
  Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Portraits" Juried Show
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T160000
UID:260217dS0EuAg070ayx6XMCJl8dg
DESCRIPTION:A juried show featuring "Portraits" ~ artworks that portray pe
