BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Treasures in Our Stacks
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T123000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T143000
UID:2603094UDPvjKw00iefJgKjl9Yug
DESCRIPTION:The Sonoma County Genealogical Society Presents\n\n **Treasur
 es in Our Stacks: Boost Your Research with a Visit to the Napa Valley Gene
 alogical Library** With Sue Ziemski\, NVGS Librarian and Susan Ingersoll\,
  NVGS President\n\n The Napa Valley Genealogical Library has more than 9\
 ,000 holdings\, many of which are rare or unique. Whether you have Napa an
 cestors or just live in Northern California\, the library probably has at 
 least one resource you didn’t know you needed.\n\nThe library\, in its p
 resent location since 1989\, is owned and operated by the Napa Valley Gene
 alogical Society. Please join us as we review the library’s holdings and
  highlight just a few of the many valuable Treasures in their stacks. You 
 just might discover more than one way that this valuable Northern Californ
 ia resource can advance your research.\n\n Susan Ingersoll and Sue Ziemsk
 i are the current President and Librarian\, respectively\, of Napa Valley 
 Genealogical Society. They have both been enthusiastic family history rese
 archers for at least a couple of decades. Like their fellow NVGS members\,
  Susan and Sue love the society’s unique library\, and enjoy spreading t
 hat love to all who will listen.\n\n Saturday\, March 21st\n\n Meeting s
 tarts at 12:30 pm\, presentation starts at 1:00 pm PST\n\nFREE\n\nVia ZOOM
 \n\nRegister at **https://www.scgsonline.org**\n\nRegistration closes Frid
 ay\, March 20th
URL:https://www.scgsonline.org 
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cloverdale Cabaret
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T213000
UID:2603092J6mB-g4d0OQ06sjDATbNw
DESCRIPTION:The Cloverdale Cabaret was born at the Cloverdale Citrus Fair 
 as a bold\, scrappy passion project—our fledgling production stepping in
 to a new chapter\, and our first without longtime director Ashlyn at the h
 elm \\(missed dearly\\). \n\nWhat began as a spark of after-hours mischief
  has grown into an intimate cabaret-in-concert that showcases the heart of
  our company: some of the incredible singers and dancers you’ve loved in
  past productions\, reunited in a more up-close\, electric setting. \n\nTh
 is cabaret leans decidedly more adult than our Citrus Fair dinner show—c
 heekier\, sultrier\, and a little dangerous—while still celebrating the 
 theatricality\, live vocals\, and ensemble magic that define us. It’s a 
 chance to see familiar performers in a new light\, telling stories through
  big songs\, bold choreography\, and unapologetic flair\, all in the heart
  of our beloved town.
LOCATION:Cloverdale Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.cloverdaleperformingarts.com/events/cloverdale-cabaret
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
