BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Park Rx-Intermediate Hiking for Fitness
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T130000
UID:26022782-bjTPhjk-b6amuBiPNZw
DESCRIPTION:If you have previously completed the Beginner Hiking f
 or Fitness Program\, or can hike a little more than 4 miles wi
 th at least 1\,000 ft of elevation\, this hiking series is for
  you! The program leaders will guide you on 8 weekly hikes wit
 h the challenge increasing each week. Leaders will have group di
 scussions about gear\, hydration\, hiking poles\, first aid and p
 acing\, etc. The group's final hike aims for Bald Mountain\, whe
 re hikers can enjoy stunning vistas.\n\nThe following is a list 
 of possible routes specifically selected for this hiking series: 
 \n\n1\\) Sat 3/7 — Creekside \\+ Waterfall loop\, 3.6 miles\, 
 750 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 2\\) Sat 3/14 – Vista
  Trail loop\, 3.4 miles\, 830 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn
 \\] 3\\) Sat 3/21 – Goodspeed to Nattkemper bench\, 3.8 miles\,
  1\,240 ft elevation \\[meet @ Goodspeed lot\\] 4\\) Sat 3/28 
 – Hillside to Neptune table \\+ Meadow\, 4.4 miles\, 970 ft e
 levation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 5\\) Sat 4/4 – Hillside \\+ V
 ista Trail loop\, 3.6 miles\, 1\,070 ft elevation \\[meet @ Whit
 e Barn\\] 6\\) Sat 4/11 – False Lake Meadow & Lake Ilsanjo lo
 op in Trionne-Annadel SP\, 6.1 miles\, 670 ft elevation \\[meet 
 @ Annadel's Cobblestone Trailhead\\] 7\\) Sat 4/18 – Fern Lake 
 \\+ Orchard loop in SDC/Jack London SHP\, 5.5 miles\, 1\,460 ft
  elevation \\[meet @ Walnut & North St inside SDC\; park on Gr
 ove St\\] 8\\) Sat 4/25 – Bald Mtn summit \\(w/optional Headwat
 ers detour\, 5.8 miles\\)\, 5.1 miles\, 1\,670 ft elevation \\[me
 et @ White Barn\\]\n\nPlease note these routes are subject to ch
 ange based on the group and weather. Wear appropriate footwear f
 or rocky or slippery trails\, and layers. Bring water\, and if 
 desired\, a snack. The group will be limited to 35 participants.
  \n\nThe hiking series costs $80 \\(plus a $10 parking fee per
  visit. Note that the Sugarloaf Annual Pass is $59 and valid a
 t Sugarloaf and Jack London SHP\\)\, or free-of-cost for particip
 ants with a January 2025 or newer Park Rx from a Sonoma County
  Medical Provider.  The number of available Park Rx tickets is
  limited\; please have your Rx ready at the time of sign up.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/park-rx-intermediate-hi
 king-for-fitness/18210471/2026-03-21T09
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Glass Menagerie
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T213000
UID:2602272MlacQsWXUGFIzxGkrtgFg
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Season at Curtain Call Theatre starts off with The Gl
 ass Menagerie\, the play that made Tennessee Williams famous.\n\nHave You 
 Ever Felt Stuck Between Your Dreams and Reality? This Play Gets It.\n\nIma
 gine being trapped in a tiny apartment during the Great Depression — no 
 money\, no way out\, just a family clinging to hopes that may never come t
 rue. That's exactly what The Glass Menagerie is about.\n\nWritten by Tenne
 ssee Williams — one of America's greatest playwrights — this story fol
 lows a restless son\, an overbearing mom\, and a painfully shy daughter as
  they each chase dreams that feel just out of reach. It's emotional\, poet
 ic\, and honestly… kind of hits different when you think about your own 
 life.\n\nThis iconic play is literally studied in classrooms worldwide\, s
 o seeing it live is like watching your textbook come to life — except wa
 y more powerful.\n\n📅 March 13–29\, 2026\n\n📍 20347 Hwy 116\, Mont
 e Rio\, CA\n\n🎟️ Grab your tickets at russianriverhall.com or call \\
 (707\\) 387-5072\n\nThe Glass Menagerie by Tennessee Williams is directed 
 by Michael Tabib.\n\nShowing at the Russian River Hall in Monte Rio\, CA f
 rom March 13-29\, 2026.\n\nProgram was made possible\, in part\, with fund
 s from Creative Sonoma and the California Arts Council \\(CAC\\).\n\nBy sp
 ecial arrangement with Dramatists Play Services\, Inc.
LOCATION:Curtain Call Theatre
URL:https://www.russianriverhall.com/2026/02/18/march-13-29-the-glass-mena
 gerie/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:MAMUSE: A Celebration of the Spring Equinox
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T000000
UID:260225JQ9F6J0Rq06NcjE37Dg4Ag
DESCRIPTION:The Muse fell from the sky one night and landed in the spaces 
 between our heart beats. She instantly took a liking to the rhythm in our 
 chests\, and her sweet melody joined the pulse. One of us picked up father
  bass\, and thumped it’s belly in response. The other picked up father m
 andolin\, and plucked its ribs. Mother guitar and sister flute could not r
 esist being a part of such sweet merriment and soon joined in.  The Earth\
 , hearing the whole incident\,  called out words of inspiration and encour
 agement.  “Yes!… keep going!”  When the Earth calls\, one must liste
 n….. So we opened our hearts and let sweet harmony roll off of our tongu
 es. In unison our voices shot out into the deep of night and a star fell f
 rom the heavens\; the magic spark!  MaMuse is born. http://www.mamuse.org 
 When you’re singing I can feel the sky and hear her never-ending lullaby
 e connecting every single point of light As I listen I’m reminded why I 
 am alive Won’t you sing it for me One more time?
LOCATION:Sebastopol Community Cultural Center
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107715145?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
