BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mercy Presents: Puff N Paint - Glow In The Dark Edition
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T220000
UID:260218w86Llme8UUG3EDO6XoRTnA
DESCRIPTION:**Mercy Presents: Puff N’ Paint – Glow In The Dark Edition
 ** *Saturday\, March 21\, 2026 | 7:00 PM – 10:00 PM* 📍 *The Lounge at
  Mercy*\n\nTap into your creative flow at **Mercy’s Glow-In-The-Dark Puf
 f N’ Paint**—a high-vibe\, black light–lit art experience where cann
 abis culture\, creativity\, and community collide inside The Lounge at Mer
 cy.\n\nThis isn’t your average paint night. Under immersive black lights
 \, neon and glow-in-the-dark paints come alive as you sip\, puff\, and cre
 ate in a relaxed\, visually electric atmosphere designed to spark imaginat
 ion and connection. Whether you’re dialed into your canvas or vibing wit
 h the room\, this session is all about expression\, conversation\, and goo
 d energy—no pressure\, just pure creative fun.\n\nGuided by smooth eveni
 ng beats\, watch your artwork transform as the lights go low and the glow 
 turns on. Expect trippy colors\, luminous strokes\, and a one-of-a-kind ma
 sterpiece you’ll take home at the end of the night.\n\nPresented by **Em
 erald Sky** and **Papa’s Herb**\, this immersive experience is your invi
 tation to slow down\, light up\, and let your creativity glow—**Mercy st
 yle**.\n\n🎨 What’s Included:\n\n\\- All glow-in-the-dark and neon pai
 nting supplies\n\n\\- Black light–powered Puff N’ Paint experience\n\n
 \\- Zero-pressure creative session\n\n\\- Take-home canvas masterpiece\n\n
 \\- Atmosphere buzzing with smooth evening beats\n\n\\- Cannabis-friendly 
 lounge to spark creativity\n\n🎟 Ticket Tiers:\n\n*Limited to 80 guests*
 \n\n**General Admission – $35** Includes paint supplies only\n\n**VIP Ti
 er 1 – $50** Includes $25 Goodie Bag\n\n**VIP Tier 2 – $75** Includes 
 $50 Goodie Bag\n\n✨ Come for the glow. Stay for the vibe. Leave with art
  that lights up the night.\n\n**21+ Only | DCC # C12-0000420-LIC**
LOCATION:The Lounge at Mercy
URL:https://www.themercylounge.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Oakmont Meets Imagination - 52 Years of Creativity
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T160000
UID:260218vleiWDwKXUG2-yl86sba_A
DESCRIPTION:This year’s show will feature the work of more than 50 membe
 rs of the Oakmont Art Association\, showcasing a rich and diverse collecti
 on of fine art. Visitors can expect to see original works in acrylic\, oil
 \, pastel\, watercolor\, fiber art\, and photography\, many of which will 
 be available for purchase. The exhibition highlights the wide range of sty
 les\, techniques\, and personal visions represented by Oakmont’s artists
 \, making each year’s show a fresh and inspiring experience.\n\nIn addit
 ion to fine art\, the show will include a lively Artisan Marketplace. Arti
 sans will offer an array of handcrafted items\, including jewelry\, photog
 raphy\, assemblage art\, fiber and fabric pieces\, original books\, potter
 y\, fused glass\, and many other unique small works. These one-of-a-kind c
 reations make perfect gifts and provide an opportunity to support local ar
 tists directly.\n\nThe event is designed to be both engaging and festive. 
 Attendees can enjoy live music by Oakmont musicians and appetizers while b
 rowsing the exhibits and visiting with artists. A popular highlight of the
  show is the annual raffle\, which adds an extra element of excitement whi
 le supporting a meaningful cause. In 2025 more than 50 raffle prizes were 
 generously donated by local businesses.  Raffle drawing and wine receptio
 n occurs at 3:30 p.m. Saturday.\n\nProceeds from the raffle benefit Art Qu
 est\, an organization that supports Santa Rosa students who are pursuing e
 ducation and careers in the arts. The generosity of past attendees has mad
 e a real impact—the 2025 raffle raised $3\,200 for Art Quest\, helping t
 o foster creativity and opportunity for young artists in our region.\n\nTh
 e Oakmont Art Association invites the community to attend this special eve
 nt\, celebrate 52 years of creativity\, and experience the imagination\, s
 kill\, and passion of its artists.
LOCATION:Berger Center
URL:http://oakmontart.com
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
