DESCRIPTION:Have you ever wanted to learn the timeless—and beautiful—a
 rt of rowing? The Floathouse crew is here for you! This season\, every Sat
 urday from January 17 to March 28\, we’ll host free rowing lessons for a
 dults. Register online\, and we’ll take you through the basics in some o
 f our stable and beautiful rowing craft: the classic Whitehall rowboat\, t
 he classy Adirondack Guideboat\, and the cute but sturdy Captain’s Gig.\
 n\nNo experience necessary\, and no $$\, either. This is our gift to you.\
 n\nThis opportunity is available to all from January though March\, 2026. 
 Come once\, come every weekend\, or just now and then. Make this the year 
 you learn to row\, on Petaluma’s Longest Park\, the Petaluma River.\n\nR
 egister online\, and we’ll see you on the dock!
