BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T180000
UID:260217GsB-i5Vw5EuoOg2FEAsvXA
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\nMARCH EXHIBIT: CELEBR
 ATING WOMEN\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\nRECEPTI
 ON: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists and ce
 lebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a 
 beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSono
 ma County artist\, Tosya Shore\, presents Celebrating Women\, paintings th
 at commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. Shore’s waterc
 olor works capture women in their element\, showing the multiple facets of
  their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with strong shapes and 
 interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways.  A la Degas\,
  we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Point.”  The arti
 st takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” where dominant trunk
  shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene.    “Just Bac
 k from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as the woman in quest
 ion catches her breath.  “There’s such special feeling in these every
 day moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – women deserve noth
 ing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore will be hosting the
  Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks
  Showcase features Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein Air\, a collection
  unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to France.  Roaming the 
 streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffer captured iconic sc
 enes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catches a true cultural v
 ibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored hangout for espresso 
 and conversation.  One is awed by the structure rising from the ground-le
 vel trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel Tower in “Paris is f
 or Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris – I hope through th
 ese plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of being there”\, stat
 ed Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Str
 eet\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 p
 m.    www.upstairsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact:
  Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Japanese Papermaking
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T170000
UID:260216ty-_zIJbsUyZ882sfLPjzQ
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026 2:00 PM – 5:00 PM Sun
 day\, March 22\, 2026 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExpe
 rience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nBilingual\, Fiber Arts\, Printmaking\n\nAge\
 \(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$180 – Registration Cost $25 – Materials Fee
  $205 – Total Registration CostLearn traditional Japanese papermaking us
 ing the nagashizuki method. Beat fiber by hand and form delicate\, strong 
 sheets to take home. All levels welcome.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nIn this wor
 kshop\, students will be introduced to the process of making Japanese pape
 r. Japanese paper\, often incorrectly referred to as rice paper\, is known
  for its great strength while appearing delicate and gossamer-thin. In thi
 s workshop\, students will learn the basics of preparing their own fiber\,
  hand beating\, and forming sheets in the traditional nagashizuki method. 
 Students will take home wet sheets to dry at home with instructions. Pleas
 e be aware that papermaking is a wet activity –  wear clothing and shoe
 s that can get wet. Class involves some physical activity\, including stan
 ding and arm movements. All supplies are provided through the materials fe
 e. La maestra habla español. Note: Please bring a bag lunch on Sunday.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/japanese-papermaking/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to Pochoir Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T160000
UID:260216kjUZV0kdGEqDa0PFp0ekPg
DESCRIPTION:Pochoir\, the French term for stencil\, is a well respected tr
 adition in book arts. Popular during the late 19th and early 20th centurie
 s\, this art-making technique was an advanced form of stencil printing. Ar
 tists would apply color pigments to paper by hand as an elegant and afford
 able way to reproduce artwork in color. Join guest artist\, Bettina Pauly 
 in this exciting one-day introduction to pochoir workshop!\n\nBettina will
  offer a short history lesson\, and share pochoir samples\, including an a
 rtist demonstration on how to use pigments with different applicators. Stu
 dents will be encouraged to learn the basics of stencil creation and will 
 work on images made up of simple shapes to practice their technique. Throu
 ghout the day\, an assortment of materials will be on hand to create stenc
 ils\; different brushes and their effects will be examined\; and various 
 ‘dry pigments’ and papers will be investigated as students expand thei
 r pochoir skills. The instructor will also lead a discussion on how studen
 ts can creatively incorporate pochoir into their own artwork\, including b
 ooks\, prints\, cards\, and more!\n\nStudents will work on a set of note c
 ards to take home and learn how to make a simple folder for the samples th
 at were made during class. The materials fee will include brushes\, stenci
 ls\, paper pigments and an assortment of paper cardstock.\n\nPlease note: 
 This class requires some hand dexterity to maneuver an exacto blade cuttin
 g knife.
LOCATION:North Bay Letterpress Arts
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/introduction-to-pochoir
 -workshop/18131340/2026-03-21T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beaded Ring Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T130000
UID:260216IYFCCARJhkmhI7nfsKIypA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026 10:00 AM – 1:00 PM\n\
 nExperience Level\n\nBeginning\n\nFiber Arts\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n13\\+\n\nChi
 ldren under the age of 18 must be accompanied by an adult.\n\n$93 – Regi
 stration Cost $7 – Materials Fee $100 – Total Registration CostDiscove
 r the ancient peyote stitch in a fun\, hands-on class and create a bold ri
 ng while learning the basics of bead weaving.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nJoin 
 us for a playful dive into an ancient craft. The peyote stitch has been us
 ed for thousands of years across many cultures. In this fun class you’ll
  create a bold beautiful ring using the Even Count Flat Peyote stitch. We
 ’ll cover everything you need to confidently start your own bead weaving
  journey. All materials \\(thread\, needles\, beads\\) will be provided fo
 r the workshop. If students would like to buy needles and thread to take h
 ome they can purchase them directly from the instructor after the workshop
  for a minimal fee. Resources for beading supplies will also be provided. 
 Finger dexterity and good close-up vision are needed for this workshop. Br
 ing your best reading glasses!\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silve
 r Memberships and above receive 10% off the registration cost for any clas
 s purchase over $40. Materials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member
  today and find community\, connection\, and creativity.\n\nLocation\n\nRo
 om 201\, Fiber Arts Studio
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/beaded-ring-workshop/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
