BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jerome Rubin and Friends : the If Not Now Fugghedaboutit Tour Retu
 rns
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T210000
UID:260212YI7ks4Kfs0CCAiRQQIzvvQ
DESCRIPTION:On Saturday March 21\, 2026 at 7pm\, the San Geronimo Valley 
 Community Center welcomes back Jerome Rubin and Friends AND the return o
 f the “If Not Now Fuhgeddaboutit Tour.” This time Jerome's bringing 
 some friends including\, Bruce Friedberg - electric accordion\, ukulele\,
  vocals\, Anthony Parber - Bass\, vocals\, Doug Martin - Lap Steel Guitar\
 , Dobro and Brad Elias - Percussion\, vocals.\n\nSince we last saw Jerome 
 play the Community Center in 2024\, he took the INNF Tour overseas. Last s
 ummer Jerome travelled all over Europe for three months of reconnecting wi
 th friends\, and successful music gatherings\, open mics and concerts in t
 he Maritimes Alpes in the south of France\, Berlin and other cities in Ger
 many\; Krakow\, Poland\, Prague\, Czech Republic\, and Strasbourg\, France
 . His return to Europe marked 50 years since he had first moved to Europe 
 in 1975 and lived for seven years.\n\nJerome Rubin has been singing since 
 birth and has performed in hundreds of concerts throughout Europe and the 
 United States. He is well known for his emotive singing voice and heartfel
 t interpretations of Bob Dylan\, Van Morrison\, Tom Waits\, American stand
 ards and many others. Jerome’s original songs and stories have won award
 s\, touched and inspired many.\n\nAnyone who saw Jerome and this band at K
 ate’s Cafe in November 2025 knows this is a show not to be missed!
LOCATION:San Geronimo Valley Community Center
URL:https://sgvperformingarts.eventcalendarapp.com/jerome-rubin-and-friend
 s
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
