BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Breathless Sparkling Wines "Women's History Celebration Sundays"
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T140000
UID:2603123uXJHc-Z8UK98VzF97uMuw
DESCRIPTION:Breathless Sparkling Wines is hosting a speaker and luncheon 
 series which will be held every Sunday in March at the winery’s tranquil
  outdoor garden in Healdsburg to honor Women’s History Month. \n\nThe 
 “Breathless Women’s History Celebration Sundays” series aligns with
  the National Women’s History Alliance’s 2026 theme\, “Leading the 
 Change: Women Shaping a Sustainable Future\,” which recognizes women adv
 ancing environmental\, economic and social sustainability through leadersh
 ip\, innovation and community impact.\n\nEach Breathless Wines Sparkling G
 arden Luncheon will be paired with a featured female speaker whose work re
 flects the evolving role of women in shaping industries and communities\, 
 sparkling wines\, and wines paired with a lunch prepared by Chef Beryl Adl
 er of Healdsburg's Acorn Café. Visit BreathlessWines.com for more.
LOCATION:Breathless Wines
URL:https://breathlesswines.com/events/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Tord Gustavsen Trio
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T220000
UID:26031218epFMKeAU2r9NLL7apESw
DESCRIPTION:A rare opportunity to be up close and personal with the Tord G
 ustavsen Trio\n\n“A Norwegian pianist of lyrical and often halcyon sensi
 bilities” \\(NY Times\\)\, Gustavsen and his trio bring a stripped-down 
 approach in which beauty and emotional intensity are united. His new ECM r
 elease\, Opening\, explores the concept of openness and taking inspiration
  from the forces that surround us.\n\nA pianist of poetic cast\, an except
 ionally lucid player with a sure sense of melodic structure and an often-a
 stonishing lyrical imagination. - JazzTimes\n\nCool and mysterious\, prist
 ine and intensely emotional\, the music of Norwegian pianist Tord Gustavse
 n has earned a vast following while making few populist concessions. Easil
 y the most acclaimed composer and pianist on the Norwegian jazz scene\, he
 ’s released a series of critically hailed albums that have climbed high 
 on the Norwegian pop charts\, starting with his 2003’s ECM debut Changin
 g Places.\n\nURLs:\n\nTickets: https://go.evvnt.com/3363109-0?pid=6298\n\n
 Website: https://go.evvnt.com/3363109-2?pid=6298\n\nFacebook: https://go.e
 vvnt.com/3363109-3?pid=6298\n\nInstagram: https://go.evvnt.com/3363109-4?p
 id=6298\n\nDate and Time: On Sun\, 22 Mar 2026 19:30 - Sun\, 22 Mar 2026 2
 2:00\n\nVenue Details: Music And Minds\, 15 Kehoe Way\, Inverness\, Califo
 rnia\, 94937\, United States\n\nCategory: Live Music\n\nPrice: Suggested D
 onation: USD 120.00\n\nArtists: TORD GUSTAVSEN\, STEINAR RAKNES \, JARLE V
 EPESTAD
LOCATION:Music And Minds
URL:http://go.evvnt.com/3363109-2?pid=6298
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Healdsburg: David Nihill Taking Tangents Tour
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T220000
UID:260311zPpb-0_s7ECKyvmz6Swf5Q
DESCRIPTION:Leaving Dublin\, Ireland where he was born and raised until th
 e age of 22\, Dave got drunk on travel and never quite hit sobriety of it.
  He has lived and worked in twelve countries and visited over seventy. His
  shows draw on his wide travels\, cultural observations\, attempts at lang
 uage study\, \\(occasional\\) international drinking session\\(s\\) and be
 ing a mildly confused immigrant. \n\nDave is the winner of the prestigious
  annual San Francisco Comedy Competition\, \\(previous finalists include R
 obin Williams\, Ellen DeGeneres and Dana Carvey\\) and runner up in the Mo
 th’s largest US Grandslam storytelling competition. He recorded his debu
 t special for Dry Bar Comedy in 2019 and has been featured on TED.com\, Th
 e Irish Independent\, Inc\, NPR\, and the Huffington Post among others. A 
 festival favourite Dave’s videos have also gone viral many times over wi
 th over 150 million views and a social following of over one million.
LOCATION:Raven Performing Arts Theater
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107563238?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
