BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Non-Toxic Comedy Show™ - Featuring Scott Schafer - No Cover
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T200000
UID:260311AOuECxJ3nkiZp0J6sfv-6g
DESCRIPTION:Tip-what-you-can comedy with headliner Scott Schafer\, plus ot
 her local faves including Hey Sienna. All the jokes with none of the traum
 a!\n\nWelcome to **NON-TOXIC COMEDY SHOW™** from **6-8 pm** at **Re
 dwood Cafe Cotati**.\n\nThis Sunday\, your hosts Sienna The Comic and Jess
 ika Frazer bring you stand-up comedy from headliner Scott Schafer with Ste
 ve Wilkes\, and Rory. Also featuring Hey Sienna\, advice from a Certified 
 Life Advice Mom - so bring your questions!\n\nThe show is No Cover\, so pl
 ease Tip What You Can to support local comedy : )\n\nAt Non-Toxic Comedy S
 how™ you’ll get all the jokes with none of the trauma!\n\nNTCS™ guar
 antees our audience CLEAN\, NON-TOXIC comedy without having to worry about
  inappropriate\, offensive\, cringeworthy content. Our CLEAN SHOW at Redwo
 od Cafe\, Cotati\, is safe for all ages\, genders\, and levels of sensitiv
 ity.\n\nDon’t get us wrong – a great set always runs the risk of offen
 ding *someone*. Who could’ve known it really *was* too soon\, *just 
 for them?*\n\nBut there are some things we here at Non-Toxic Comedy Show
 ™ think are *always* too soon and will *never* age well. At NTCS you
 'll never hear anything hateful or malicious \, or jokes that punch down. 
 Plus we keep things PG clean!\n\nRespectful innuendo is just funnier. The 
 writing is hard\, the material is smart\, the laughter is real. That's the
  toxic-free guarantee! We guarantee our audience Non-Toxic\, family-safe c
 omedy.\n\nWhile we trust our performers to adhere to these guidelines\, if
  a joke seems like it's about to cross the line\, the performer will be cu
 t off with a cowbell\, and may not be invited back. Our goal at Non-Toxic 
 Comedy Show™? No Cowbell!
LOCATION:Redwood Cafe
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/non-toxic-comedy-showtm-featuring-scott-s
 chafer-no-cover-tickets-1984938783334?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=atte
 ndeeshare&utm-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshco
 pyurl
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cloverdale Cabaret
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T140000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T160000
UID:260309kwTvCigqCEujLvvHT-jbQQ
DESCRIPTION:The Cloverdale Cabaret was born at the Cloverdale Citrus Fair 
 as a bold\, scrappy passion project—our fledgling production stepping in
 to a new chapter\, and our first without longtime director Ashlyn at the h
 elm \\(missed dearly\\). \n\nWhat began as a spark of after-hours mischief
  has grown into an intimate cabaret-in-concert that showcases the heart of
  our company: some of the incredible singers and dancers you’ve loved in
  past productions\, reunited in a more up-close\, electric setting. \n\nTh
 is cabaret leans decidedly more adult than our Citrus Fair dinner show—c
 heekier\, sultrier\, and a little dangerous—while still celebrating the 
 theatricality\, live vocals\, and ensemble magic that define us. It’s a 
 chance to see familiar performers in a new light\, telling stories through
  big songs\, bold choreography\, and unapologetic flair\, all in the heart
  of our beloved town.
LOCATION:Cloverdale Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.cloverdaleperformingarts.com/events/cloverdale-cabaret
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Two Painters in the Garden: Alina Nuebel and Frances McCormack
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T160000
UID:260306mBX7HqFBREKn_dS-G61hHg
DESCRIPTION:Two Painters in the Garden is a rich and varied exhibition of 
 work by two accomplished Sonoma artists who distill the essence of the nat
 ural world through bold and semi-abstract interpretations of trees\, liche
 ns\, birds' nests\, and more. The exhibition is a deep immersion into the 
 energies and strategies of the natural world. Exhibition opening reception
  March 21\, 5-7 pm. Free and open to the public. Come celebrate the beauty
  of spring in Sonoma with us!
LOCATION:Alley Gallery
URL:https://www.alley.gallery
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T000000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T120000
UID:260306OhQIEuHfMEWcfgKv5oovcw
DESCRIPTION:**Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challe
 nge" (online).** \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\n**Only
  $5**\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\n***M
 arch Month of Flowers* Challenge** is here to give you a creative outlet
 \, some structure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a b
 rush\, pen\, or pencil (thread\, clay\, fabric…)\, your brain gets a res
 t and becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more 
 alive\; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Y
 our intuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curios
 ity grows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you fi
 nd the freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
