UID:260227VMcozuevwES4pCN8EssYgw
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T180000
UID:2602179TYf_wdyzkSGohJBAbvByA
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\nMARCH EXHIBIT: CELEBR
 ATING WOMEN\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\nRECEPTI
 ON: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists and ce
 lebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a 
 beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSono
 ma County artist\, Tosya Shore\, presents Celebrating Women\, paintings th
 at commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. Shore’s waterc
 olor works capture women in their element\, showing the multiple facets of
  their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with strong shapes and 
 interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways.  A la Degas\,
  we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Point.”  The arti
 st takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” where dominant trunk
  shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene.    “Just Bac
 k from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as the woman in quest
 ion catches her breath.  “There’s such special feeling in these every
 day moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – women deserve noth
 ing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore will be hosting the
  Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks
  Showcase features Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein Air\, a collection
  unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to France.  Roaming the 
 streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffer captured iconic sc
 enes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catches a true cultural v
 ibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored hangout for espresso 
 and conversation.  One is awed by the structure rising from the ground-le
 vel trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel Tower in “Paris is f
 or Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris – I hope through th
 ese plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of being there”\, stat
 ed Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Str
 eet\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 p
 m.    www.upstairsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact:
  Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Adult Gymnastics Class
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T183000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260324T200000
UID:260214t4nYNuWg-0aHcYN5pHxdCQ
DESCRIPTION:**We’re offering Adult Gymnastics Classes for the 18+ crowd!
 **\n\n**Adult Gymnastics classes occur every Tuesday 5:00 PM to 6:30 PM &
  Friday from 6:30 PM to 8:00 PM.**\n\n**$20 per person\, OR pay for a wh
 ole 8-week session in advance through our site. You can attend on Tuesday\
 , Friday\, or both!**\n\n**Please bring the class fee in cash at the time 
 of arrival. This can be a DROP IN\, so there is no need to sign up online 
 before coming!**\n\nIf you’ve ever wanted to try out gymnastics or get b
 ack into it in adulthood\, now is your chance! During our adult classes\, 
 open to all genders\, our coaches will move at the pace of each student\, 
 helping them achieve goals they set for themselves. **No experience is ne
 cessary** to be involved in this class\, so this is a great opportunity t
 o learn the basics and get some exercise\, no matter what age you are! Try
  out our trampoline\, bars\, beam\, and other gym equipment in a safe and 
 supportive environment. You can build strength and increase your range of 
 motion while having fun like you’re a kid again.\n\nAsk our coaches what
  you can work on between classes\, and they’ll help personalize your tra
 ining!\n\nPlease wear something comfortable and keep long hair tied back. 
 Skirts and restrictive clothing are not recommended. You must remove your 
 shoes before going onto the mat or using equipment. Please let us know if 
 you have any physical limitations or health conditions that may interfere 
 with doing certain motions. We recommend bringing a water bottle.\n\nYou c
 an email us for more info or join our mailing list at: info@sonomagymnast
 icsacademy.com
LOCATION:Sonoma Gymnastics Academy
URL:https://sonomagymnasticsacademy.com/home/adult-gymnastics-night/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
