UID:260210GGHzGrTEGku70Ec84rThGQ
DESCRIPTION:Tuesdays\, February 10 – April 7\, 2026 4:00 PM – 6:00 PM 
 Exception: No class March 24\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nKids\, T
 eens\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n10-15\n\n$360 – Registration CostPresented by the 
 Sonoma Community Center in partnership with The Game Academy\n\nJoin Adven
 ture Gaming classes with The Game Academy! Play D&D\, build community\, an
 d grow empathy through weekly storytelling sessions.\n\nAbout the class\n\
 nclass descriptionAdventure Gaming classes presented by The Game Academy a
 re held weekly for 2-hour sessions over an 8-week term. Participating pl
 ayers explore collaborative storytelling in a mentorship model using game
 s like Dungeons & Dragons to build community\, foster empathy\, and suppo
 rt social-emotional growth. Our trained Educator-Gamemasters guide players
  in choosing the kinds of stories that interest them\, then support unique
  and dynamic character creation\, and finally present an engaging narrati
 ve filled with puzzles and mysteries to be solved\, social role-play to na
 vigate\, and tactical challenges to be overcome… all based on the playe
 rs’ interests. This uniquely tailored experience provides a rich conte
 xt of personal investment\, and engages our players with a fun and collabo
 rative activity that helps them overcome social and emotional challenges\,
  teaches them to engage with a growth mindset\, supports the development o
 f critical thinking and cooperative problem-solving skills\, and helps the
 m form lasting bonds with their peers. We hope your child will join us for
  a new adventure this coming Fall Term at the Sonoma Community Center.\n\n
 Pick-up Service\n\nWe also offer a free pick-up service for your kids if y
 ou are unable to drop them off after school. More more information\, pleas
 e contact Melissa Agocs at melissa@sonomacommunitycenter.org.\n\nMembersh
 ip has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above receive 10% off th
 e registration cost for any class purchase over $40. Materials fees are no
 t discounted.\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 211\, Conference Room
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
