BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T180000
UID:2602175z25HdQxwEu_cDoAOVmrqQ
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\nMARCH EXHIBIT: CELEBR
 ATING WOMEN\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\nRECEPTI
 ON: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists and ce
 lebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a 
 beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.\n\nSono
 ma County artist\, Tosya Shore\, presents Celebrating Women\, paintings th
 at commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. Shore’s waterc
 olor works capture women in their element\, showing the multiple facets of
  their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with strong shapes and 
 interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways.  A la Degas\,
  we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Point.”  The arti
 st takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” where dominant trunk
  shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene.    “Just Bac
 k from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as the woman in quest
 ion catches her breath.  “There’s such special feeling in these every
 day moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – women deserve noth
 ing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore will be hosting the
  Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Stairway Smallworks
  Showcase features Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein Air\, a collection
  unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to France.  Roaming the 
 streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffer captured iconic sc
 enes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catches a true cultural v
 ibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored hangout for espresso 
 and conversation.  One is awed by the structure rising from the ground-le
 vel trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel Tower in “Paris is f
 or Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris – I hope through th
 ese plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of being there”\, stat
 ed Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hosting the Gallery on M
 arch 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Center Str
 eet\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. \\(707\\) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 p
 m.    www.upstairsart gallery.net \n\nFor further information: Contact:
  Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: Celebrating Women
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260325T180000
UID:260213rIqxeGKDuUST3VFO-kg5Rw
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  2/13/26\n\n**MARCH EXHIBIT: CELE
 BRATING WOMEN**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  February 23 – March 29\, 2026\n\n**R
 ECEPTION: SATURDAY\, MARCH 7\, 2026\, 4-6 pm: Join in to meet the artists 
 and celebrate the show. Take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing 
 for a beautiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**
 \n\nSonoma County artist\, **Tosya Shore\,** presents **Celebrating Women\
 ,** paintings that commemorate women in honor of Women’s History Month. 
 Shore’s watercolor works capture women in their element\, showing the mu
 ltiple facets of their lives.  These dynamic paintings break away with st
 rong shapes and interlacing patterns that draw the viewer in exciting ways
 .  A la Degas\, we catch a ballet dancer lacing her shoes in “Good Poin
 t.”  The artist takes us into nature with “Redwood Rendezvous” wher
 e dominant trunk shapes frame a couple enjoying a glorious forest scene. 
    “Just Back from Vegas” captures a fleeting view of elegance as th
 e woman in question catches her breath.  “There’s such special feelin
 g in these everyday moments\, I love to turn the mundane into magic – wo
 men deserve nothing less\,” noted Shore. \n\nMeet the artist: Shore wil
 l be hosting the Gallery on March 5 and 19 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\n The Sta
 irway Smallworks Showcase features **Donna Schaffer’s Ooh La La\, Plein 
 Air\,** a collection unveiling oil paintings made on her recent trip to Fr
 ance.  Roaming the streets of Paris\, toting paints and palette\, Schaffe
 r captured iconic scenes buzzing with “la belle vie.” The viewer catch
 es a true cultural vibe in “Café le Bistro”\, the site of a favored h
 angout for espresso and conversation.  One is awed by the structure risin
 g from the ground-level trees in Schaffer’s unique view of the Eiffel To
 wer in “Paris is for Lovers.” “Every day was an adventure in Paris 
 – I hope through these plein air vignettes\, to share the excitement of 
 being there”\, stated Schaffer.\n\nMeet the artist: Schaffer will be hos
 ting the Gallery on March 21 and 22 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nUpstairs Art Gal
 lery\, 306 Center Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DA
 ILY: 11am – 6 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further 
 information: Contact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net o
 r 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
