BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bottle Baby Breakfast Club
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T160000
UID:260312aBF7qTUwOEGQ20x3CENgbg
DESCRIPTION:Tiny Hooves\, Big Hearts: Our Ongoing Rescue Mission\n\nAt Goa
 tlandia\, our mission is simple: to give love\, safety\, and a second chan
 ce to animals who need it most.\n\nWe were recently called to rescue three
  baby goats. These tiny babies are now safe at Goatlandia\, and they need 
 bottle feeding several times a day to stay healthy and thrive.\n\nThat’s
  Where You Come In: The Bottle Baby Breakfast Club\n\nStarting March 6th\,
  join us for a heartwarming hour on the farm\, bottle-feeding and cuddling
  our newest rescues while supporting their care.\n\nYour $250 donation \\(
 covers milk and supplies for weeks of feedings\\) includes admission for u
 p to four guests for a private\, unforgettable visit to Goatlandia.\n\nCom
 e share the love\, feel the magic\, and help us give these little ones the
  future they deserve.
LOCATION:Goatlandia
URL:https://www.goatlandia.org/bottle-babies-breakfast-club
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Imaginists present The Naturalists a new play by Jon Bernson
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T220000
UID:260309CIqaeU3JK0my46xI_ed7gA
DESCRIPTION:The Imaginists present a new play by Jon Bernson about a reclu
 sive group of scientists whose radical discoveries challenge widely held a
 ssumptions about the world.The play unfolds across two interwoven timeline
 s: in the present\, the audience witnesses a sequence of high-stakes lectu
 res\, as each scientist unveils work that promises to reshape reality itse
 lf. Between these presentations\, the story flashes back to the week befor
 e the summit\, marked by the recent death of one of the Naturalists and es
 calating financial strain that threatens their fragile order.
LOCATION:The Imaginists
URL:https://theimaginists.org/the-naturalists-march-april
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Young People's Chamber Orchestra
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T213000
UID:260308xpxfLT7trEKMuB8Wj7SSJw
DESCRIPTION:The Young People’s Chamber Orchestra is a youth string orch
 estra working without a conductor. It is modeled after the Bay Area’s re
 nowned New Century Chamber Orchestra and is the first youth ensemble of it
 s kind in northern California. Currently under the direction of Aaron Wes
 tman\, the orchestra has been featured as a guest on a New Century Chamber
  Orchestra performance and has been a winner of the Berkeley Junior Bach F
 estival.
LOCATION:Cloverdale Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.cloverdaleperformingarts.com/events/the-young-peoples-cham
 ber-orchestra
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Two Painters in the Garden: Alina Nuebel and Frances McCormack
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T160000
UID:260306txDfA-3tuEK9OF9uexUmOA
DESCRIPTION:Two Painters in the Garden is a rich and varied exhibition of 
 work by two accomplished Sonoma artists who distill the essence of the nat
 ural world through bold and semi-abstract interpretations of trees\, liche
 ns\, birds' nests\, and more. The exhibition is a deep immersion into the 
 energies and strategies of the natural world. Exhibition opening reception
  March 21\, 5-7 pm. Free and open to the public. Come celebrate the beauty
  of spring in Sonoma with us!
LOCATION:Alley Gallery
URL:https://www.alley.gallery
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T000000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T120000
UID:2603067O8Y7Xr7BU-Jk-i1gK-Pig
DESCRIPTION:**Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challe
 nge" (online).** \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\n**Only
  $5**\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\n***M
 arch Month of Flowers* Challenge** is here to give you a creative outlet
 \, some structure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a b
 rush\, pen\, or pencil (thread\, clay\, fabric…)\, your brain gets a res
 t and becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more 
 alive\; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Y
 our intuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curios
 ity grows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you fi
 nd the freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T220000
UID:260305eu5j5Kzr1kCIStGFxMLYeQ
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-27T19
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
