BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:T-Bone N Weasel - Live Theatre at THE 222 / Healdsburg
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T190000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T190000
UID:2602191fGl8xoedEu6vWfFPPJx3w
DESCRIPTION:**T**he play follows the antic peregrinations of two ex-convic
 ts as they make their erratic way across South Carolina in search of a hot
  meal or an easy mark.\n\nHoping to bring themselves up to at least the po
 verty level\, two ex-convicts\, T Bone (who is Black) and Weasel (who is W
 hite) have stolen a rather decrepit Buick and have set off across South Ca
 rolina with minor mayhem in mind. Moving swiftly from one adventure to an
 other\, they botch an attempted robbery\,  are swindled out of the Buick 
 by a fast-talking used car dealer\, run afoul of a sexually voracious lady
  farmer\, fall into the clutches of a larcenous country preacher\, and try
  to make off with the automobile of a politically ambitious small town doc
 tor who wants to exhibit them as examples of what poverty can do to people
 . Then it is back on the road again…\n\n*Every time they try to break th
 e law\, the law breaks them. A tale of two idiots\, smartly told by playwr
 ight Jon Klein\, “T-Bone n Weasel” is kind of like a good road-kill: i
 t’s funny\, gross and makes a lasting impression.* — Variety\n\nFeatur
 ing:\n\nT-Bone – Aldo Billingslea\n\nWeasel – Timothy Redman\n\nVerna 
 Mae – Sylvia Burboeck\n\n***Sponsored by Linda Hillel & Jon Eisenberg an
 d Malin Giddings & Richard Hechler***\n\nTheatre - Programmed by Aldo Bill
 ingslea and Amy Kossow\n\nTHE 222 / 222 Healdsburg Avenue / Healdsburg CA
LOCATION:THE 222 / Healdsburg
URL:https://the222.org/product/t-bone-n-weasel/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
