BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Comedy Night at Cloverdale Performing Arts Center - Featuring Joe 
 Klocek
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T193000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T213000
UID:260308MMWqI7-iPUiuX4EovjjfoQ
DESCRIPTION:Joe is a square peg in a round hole sort of guy. Raised a Midw
 esterner\, so he has manners\, but living in San Francisco for more than 3
 0 years\, so he thinks he's better than you. Joe does two things great —
  tells stories and talks to the crowd.\n\nJoe currently runs two monthly s
 hows in San Francisco. At Cobbs Comedy Club\, his game show\, “Get It!?
 ” is becoming the next big thing. At The Punch Line\, Joe Klocek & Frien
 ds\, is his chance to show off new talent to audiences and headline.\n\nJo
 e had a two month "comic in residency" at the first comedy club in Shangha
 i\, China.\n\nJoe has been featured on NPR's\, "Snap Judgement" and has al
 so appeared on Comedy Central's "Live at Gotham\," NBC's "Last Comic Stand
 ing\," and was commentator for the Emmy award winning documentary\, "A Bri
 dge So Far."\n\nJoe has also been a runner-up in the "San Francisco Intern
 ational Comedy Competition" and the "Seattle Comedy Competition." \n\nVot
 ed "Best Comic" in the SF Weekly Readers Poll.
LOCATION:Cloverdale Performing Arts Center
URL:https://www.cloverdaleperformingarts.com/events/comedy-night-joe-kloce
 k
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T000000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T120000
UID:260306q8Xxm5z0qEqOlutl7VRqJw
DESCRIPTION:**Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challe
 nge" (online).** \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\n**Only
  $5**\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\n***M
 arch Month of Flowers* Challenge** is here to give you a creative outlet
 \, some structure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a b
 rush\, pen\, or pencil (thread\, clay\, fabric…)\, your brain gets a res
 t and becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more 
 alive\; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Y
 our intuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curios
 ity grows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you fi
 nd the freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
