BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Overeaters Anonymous (OA) Newcomer Meeting
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T094500
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T101500
UID:260212A5qvNY6oekeKSFLby51dxA
DESCRIPTION:Is Food a Problem for You? You Are Not Alone.\n\nOvereaters An
 onymous \\(OA\\) is a fellowship of people who support each other in recov
 ering from compulsive eating and food behaviors. If you feel you have a pr
 oblem with food\, OA welcomes you—no matter what your background\, belie
 fs\, or eating habits. \n\nWe hold an in-person newcomer meeting on first
 \, second and fourth Saturdays of the month from 9:45 - 10:15 AM at ​Uni
 tarian Universalist Congregation of Marin\, 240 Channing Way\, San Rafael 
 CA 94903. Contact: Sue M. 415-298-6792​. You may view all North Bay OA 
 in-person and online meetings at https://www.northbayoa.org/meetings.html\
 n\nIn OA\, members experience spiritual\, emotional\, and physical recover
 y by practicing the Twelve Steps and living by their spiritual principles
 —one day at a time.\n\nOA is not a diet club or calorie-counting program
 .\n\nMembers have different plans of eating.\n\nOA does not endorse any sp
 ecific food plan. \n\nIf food is causing problems in your life\, you don
 ’t have to struggle alone. Recovery is possible\, and help is available.
 \n\nVisit: https://www.northbayoa.org/\n\nFind a meeting: https://www.nort
 hbayoa.org/meetings.html
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalist Congregation of Marin
URL:https://www.northbayoa.org/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Saturday Live Music at Spicy Vines feat. Adam Lieb
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T150000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T180000
UID:260205xv1wWCL3PkavJoazZ6elkg
DESCRIPTION:*Where unforgettable wines\, live music\, and good vibes come 
 together.*\n\nJoin us every Saturday from 3–6 PM at Spicy Vines for a ta
 sting room experience like no other — where top local musicians from acr
 oss the Bay Area meet our award-winning small-lot wines. From Rock & Roll 
 and Blues to Jazz\, Bluegrass\, and Americana\, each weekend brings new so
 unds and new reasons to raise a glass. \n\n**Adam Lieb**\n\nBlending rock
 \, blues\, soul\, and global folk influences\, singer-songwriter and guita
 rist Adam Lieb delivers music infused with passion\, craftsmanship\, and
  deep cultural roots.\n\n **Details**\n\nNo cover. Walk-ins are welcome\,
  but this event tends to fill up quickly\, so we recommend making a reserv
 ation. We are dog and family friendly!
LOCATION:Spicy Vines Winery
URL:https://spicyvines.com/event/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Year to Live
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T130000
UID:251217QPY7A6yiW0GalpwoX-j7gw
DESCRIPTION:with Vinny Ferraro\, Frank Ostaseski and Pam Dunn\n\nThis year
 long journey\, inspired by Stephen Levine’s A Year to Live\, is a heart
 felt invitation to people of all ages\, at any stage of life. Together\, i
 n the spirit of community\, we will explore how contemplating death can pr
 ofoundly deepen our experience of living.\n\nIn our modern world\, where w
 e often shy away from the reality of our mortality\, we rarely pause to co
 nsider the preciousness of each moment. The Buddha encouraged us to reflec
 t on death not out of fear\, but as a way to awaken to the fleeting beauty
  of our lives. By embracing this practice\, we come to appreciate the frag
 ility and impermanence of our existence.\n\nThis program is a yearlong exp
 loration of forgiveness\, gratitude\, and letting go. Through guided medit
 ations\, thoughtful inquiry\, and intimate group discussions\, we will sup
 port one another in discovering what death has to teach us about life and 
 vice versa.\n\nProgram Includes\n\nFormat: Online via Zoom \\(must know ho
 w to join a specific breakout room manually\\)\n\nTeachings: Monthly \\(12
 \\) large group sessions \\(attendance at 10 of 12 live sessions required\
 ; this must include the first session on Jan 31st\\)\n\nHome Groups \\(req
 uired!\\): Monthly \\(12\\)\, 1-hour\, self-facilitated\, self-hosted Home
  Groups that meet in between large group sessions. They are a foundational
  aspect of this program and will be organized by Spirit Rock. Each group w
 ill determine a time/day and location \\(online or in-person\\) that works
  for everyone during the January large group session.\n\nHome practice: Gu
 ided meditations\, readings\, reflections \\(estimated 5-7 hours/month \\
 + monthly Home Groups \\+ daily meditation\\)\n\nAccess: Video and audio r
 ecording access for 1 year after program ends via our Online Learning Plat
 form\n\nQ&As: Monthly\, 1-hour\, recorded \\(optional\\)
LOCATION:Spirit Rock Meditation Center
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/a-year-to-live/17585585
 /2026-03-28T10
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bachata Beginners Saturday
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T100000
UID:251213FEjbJM7M_0-u_CcNz6vdOg
DESCRIPTION:This class is perfect for bachata beginners that want to learn
  basic steps and skills\, or those who want to refresh their foundational 
 skills. We understand that learning something new can feel a little intimi
 dating. That’s why our supportive and relaxed environment is specificall
 y designed to make learning bachata basics an absolute blast!\n\nOur frien
 dly instructors will guide you through:\n\nBasic directional steps: You
 ’ll learn the fundamental movements that form the building blocks of all
  bachata dancing.\n\nProper frame for partner work: Discover how to conne
 ct comfortably and effectively with a partner\, setting you up for smooth 
 and enjoyable dances.\n\nSimple turn patterns: We’ll introduce you to e
 asy-to-follow turn patterns that will have you dancing with a partner in n
 o time.\n\nWe’ve carefully organized our curriculum to ensure that each 
 movement is easy to grasp and remember\, building your confidence with eve
 ry step. Our goal is to make learning fun. Join us to learn Bachata in Mar
 in.\n\nImportant Details\n\nNo dance experience required: Whether you’v
 e never danced before or it’s been a while\, you’re welcome here!\n\nN
 o partner necessary: Come solo or bring a friend—either way\, you’ll 
 have plenty of opportunities to dance.\n\nPlease wear non-marking shoe so
 les: This helps us keep our dance floor in great condition.\n\nCome join 
 us and discover the joy of bachata! We can’t wait to see you on the danc
 e floor.\n\nDate & Time:\n\nThursdays @ 6:30PM – 7:30PM Fridays @ 5:30PM
  – 6:30PM Saturdays @ 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM\n\nInstructor: Lucie Ebnerova
 \n\nAddress: 4140 Redwood Highway \\#8 San Rafael\, CA\n\nNote: Arrive 10 
 minutes before. No floor marking shoe soles allowed.
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8 San Rafael
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/bachata-beginners/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Salsa Beginner Marin – Saturday
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T110000
UID:251212LcqjZImALEK1KmDUplVinQ
DESCRIPTION:**Ready to learn intermediate steps and technique?** Join on 
 on Saturday – Salsa Beginner Marin\n\nAre you a beginner who’s always 
 wanted to learn salsa? Salsa classes are designed to help you build a stro
 ng foundation. In this class\, you’ll learn the fundamental footwork\, p
 ractice the basic turns\, and understand the essential body movement that 
 will make you feel confident on the dance floor. This class is perfect for
  anyone ready to learn the techniques and foundational steps needed to sta
 rt their salsa journey.\n\nSalsa is fun\, and we make learning it stress-f
 ree! Our relaxed\, beginner-friendly class is the ideal starting point. Yo
 u don’t need a partner\, nor any dance experience!\n\nIn this class you 
 will learn:\n\nBasic directional steps that form the foundation of salsa.\
 n\nProper frame for comfortable and effective partner-work.\n\nSimple\, ea
 sy-to-remember turn patterns.\n\nGet ready to learn the fundamentals and h
 ave a great time!\n\n**Details:**\n\n**No partner necessary**—rotations 
 ensure everyone dances\n\nPlease wear **non-marking shoes** to protect t
 he floor\n\nArrive 10 minutes early\; warm up and settle in\n\n**When:** 
 Saturday\, 10:00 am – 11:00 am\n\n**Where:** 4140 Redwood Highway #8\, 
 San Rafael\, CA
LOCATION:4140 Redwood Highway #8\, San Rafael\, CA
URL:https://salsadancemarin.com/salsa-beginners-saturday/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
