BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Flora & Fauna - Watercolor Course with Hannah Day
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T160000
UID:2601132pvzrdj76UOMW8UIomlgMA
DESCRIPTION:In this 4 week course\, participants will learn a unique appro
 ach to watercolor\, intended to alleviate the frustration that many experi
 ence when learning this beautiful yet challenging medium. The class will f
 ocus on strengthening one’s observational skills\, giving the artist a f
 oundation off of which to build their paintings in a step by step layering
  process\, that trains the artist to see value and color\n\nOur subject ma
 tter will be flora and fauna - a sampling of plants and animals. These sub
 jects are great for beginners and experienced artists alike\; their organi
 c shapes make them forgiving drawing subjects\, but their beauty can be a 
 muse for life. \n\nThis class will work both from photographs and from li
 fe\, practicing observational drawing in addition to watercolor technique.
  With 4 class sessions\, participants will have the opportunity to develop
  their skills and build muscle memory with a medium that often feels like 
 it has a mind of its own. \n\nAll materials provided.\n\nLocation: Bohemi
 an Flowers Farm\, 121 Bohemian Hwy\, Freestone\, CA\n\nDates: Four Sundays
  - March 8\, 15\, 22\, 29\n\nTime: 1 - 4 pm\n\nAges: Adults\n\nSkill Level
 s: All Levels
LOCATION:Bohemian Flowers Farm
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/flora-fauna-watercolor-
 course-with-hannah-day/17871651/2026-03-29T13
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
