BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Americana Afternoon - Mark McLay & The Dustdevils
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T130000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T150000
UID:260303WR0oNKSkUUyCPA10xQ7ugA
DESCRIPTION:Heartland rock with grit and soul\, Mark McLay & The Dustdevil
 s deliver songs that hit home. Mark McLay & The Dustdevils play American r
 ock and roll rooted in the storytelling tradition of John Hiatt\, Jackson 
 Browne\, and Bruce Springsteen. Mark’s nuanced\, expressive vocals carry
  tuneful melodies and meaningful lyrics\, wrapped in sophisticated\, song-
 first arrangements that balance grit\, heart\, and hope. Backed by the sea
 soned Dustdevils—veterans of the stage and studio—the band moves effor
 tlessly from hard-nosed rock to tender\, reflective moments\, always in se
 rvice of the song. Praised by critics at KRSH\, KPFA\, and the North Bay B
 ohemian\, their honest\, evocative sound has been featured in film\, TV\, 
 and radio—and it’s even better live. Doors Open: 12:30 PM | Show Start
 s: 1:00 PM Tickets $17 in advance. $25 at door
LOCATION:The California
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/795332332840173/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Spirit of Lennon
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T213000
UID:260303OMhAJPhq0kWouilV5g6MlA
DESCRIPTION:An intimate acoustic tribute to the life and music of John Len
 non In the Spirit of Lennon is Drew Harrison’s intimate acoustic tribute
  to John Lennon\, and interpretation of his music. Drew goes beyond just s
 ounding like Lennon\, capturing the intensity and delicate honesty that Le
 nnon brought to the music of The Beatles\, as well as his solo work betwee
 n 1970-1980. There is much you’ve never known about John Lennon. John Le
 nnon: Unplugged. Hear Lennon’s songs as Lennon intended\, and the storie
 s behind them! Featuring Tommy Cosentino at piano. “Drew has a great voi
 ce! His Lennon is impeccable! I feel like I am in the room with Lennon him
 self!” - Bob Brown - Owner of Rancho Nicasio / Artist Management: Angela
  Strehli\, Pablo Cruise\, & Huey Lewis & The News PURCHASE IN ADVANCE AND 
 SAVE! PLUS RESERVE A TABLE WITH OUR ZONE TICKET OPTION Reserved seating in
  Zone A  $35\, Zone B $30\, Zone C $25 \\(does not guarantee seating\\) Ti
 ckets at the door $35.  Zone C only available Doors open 5:00pm.
LOCATION:528 7th St
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/834126189493513/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
