 xplore the park after dark this April Fools' day. This hike hea
 ds up to the summit of Bald Mountain\, where we will see the 
 moon rise over the Mayacamas and the sun set over Sonoma Valley
 . This is a strenuous hike of approximately 6.5 miles with 1500
 \\+ of vertical and some steep sections \\(not recommended for c
 hildren under 12\\).\n\nMeet at the White Barn parking lot at le
 ast 10 minutes prior to the start time. Tickets are $10 general
  or $5 for youth \\(12-17 year olds\\)\, students\, Sugarloaf me
 mbers\, and Sugarloaf and RFO volunteers. All minors must be acc
 ompanied by a parent or legal guardian. You must register to at
 tend\; tickets will not be available on site. Bring your flashli
 ght\, at least a quart of water\, snacks\, and extra layers for
  the evening. Parking fees apply.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/fools-moon-hike/1824353
 2/2026-04-01T17
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T090000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T180000
UID:260227njqf_RCO_028hGamyB3BSQ
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cedar Roots
