BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Triduum and Easter Celebrations
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T200000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T210000
UID:260218EgXvSYzmgkmQ2r0CHxiZXw
DESCRIPTION:As we approach the highest holy days of the Christian year\, w
 e warmly invite you to join St. Columba’s\, Inverness for the celebratio
 n of the Sacred Triduum\, culminating in the joy of Easter Sunday. The Tri
 duum \\(Latin for “three days”\\) is one continuous liturgy unfolding 
 over Maundy Thursday\, Good Friday\, and the Great Vigil of Easter. Togeth
 er\, these services celebrate the history of salvation from Creation to Re
 demption. A history of Love poured out\, suffering faced with courage\, de
 ath held in hope\, and new life in the most unexpected of places. \n\nAll
  services are open to the public.\n\nMaundy Thursday – April 1 | 8:00 pm
 \n\nLiturgy & Washing of the Feet\n\nWe gather to remember Jesus’ final 
 meal with his friends and his commandment to love through humble service. 
 The washing of feet invites us into vulnerability\, care\, and shared huma
 nity.\n\nGood Friday – April 2 | 12:00 pm & 3:00 pm\n\n12:00 pm – Outd
 oor Ecological Way of the Cross\n\nWe walk together outdoors\, praying wit
 h creation and reflecting on suffering\, grief\, and our shared responsibi
 lity for the healing of the earth.\n\n3:00 pm – Veneration of the Cross 
 \\(in the nave\\)\n\nA solemn and spacious liturgy where we honor the myst
 ery of the cross and the depth of Christ’s love.\n\nHoly Saturday – Ap
 ril 3 | 8:00 pm\n\nThe Great Vigil of Easter & Celebratory Reception\n\nBe
 ginning in darkness\, we tell the great stories of salvation\, light the n
 ew fire\, renew baptismal promises\, and proclaim the Resurrection. A cele
 bratory reception follows as we rejoice together.\n\nEaster Sunday – Apr
 il 4 | 10:00 am\n\nLiturgy of the Resurrection & Easter Brunch\n\nWe celeb
 rate the triumph of life over death\, hope over despair\, and love over fe
 ar. Easter Brunch follows. Come and feast with us.\n\nIf you are longing f
 or meaning\, beauty\, or hope in these dark days\, you belong here. Come a
 s you are. Bring a friend. Walk with us from the table to the cross and th
 e empty tomb.
LOCATION:St. Columba's Inverness
URL:https://www.stcolumbasinverness.org/triduum
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Poetry Month Writing & Printing Workshop Series
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T203000
UID:260216oHViGaEgoEig0s2nC4BWBg
DESCRIPTION:Each week\, we’ll warm up with guided poetry prompts and gro
 up workshopping\, then move into spontaneous composition using movable met
 al and wood type. You’ll set short poems by hand\, experiment with layou
 t and typography\, and print your work on the press—embracing the beauti
 ful constraints and surprises of letterpress.\n\nAs the weeks progress\, w
 e’ll curate and print a collaborative chapbook featuring original poems 
 from everyone in the group. The final result will be a shared\, tactile pu
 blication that reflects a month of creative exchange\, ink-stained hands\,
  and collective storytelling.\n\nNo prior letterpress or poetry experience
  is required—just curiosity\, openness\, and a willingness to play with 
 language and form. Whether you’re a seasoned poet or brand new to writin
 g\, this workshop offers space to experiment\, connect\, and make somethin
 g meaningful together.\n\nAll materials included. Participants will receiv
 e copies of the finished chapbook.
LOCATION:North Bay Letterpress Arts
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/poetry-month-writing-pr
 inting-workshop-series/18131346/2026-04-01T18
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Next-Level Drawing
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T110000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T130000
UID:260210gzKlu_-aSkygtTzRLqRNDw
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nWednesday\, March 11 – April 22\, 2026 11:00 AM 
 – 1:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 208\n\nExperience Level\n\nIntermediate\n\
 nDrawing & Painting\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n18 and older\n\n$225 – Registration
  CostAdvance your drawing skills with deep study of composition\, value\, 
 and technique. Strengthen your creative process through focused practice.\
 n\nAbout the Class\n\nIn this class\, we will explore composition\, value\
 , and other aspects of drawing but on a deeper level. Beginning drawing cl
 asses have a lot of ground to cover so the concepts are skimmed over in or
 der to give you exposure to as many as possible. Next-level drawing takes 
 the time to do a deeper dive into some of the principles of drawing. When 
 drawing we use limited tools which allow us to isolate both our strengths 
 and weaknesses. Using this opportunity to really investigate our own proce
 ss will serve to strengthen all aspects of our creative work. Drawing can 
 be a challenge but when you see how it enhances the creative process\, you
  will know it is worth it. This class is suitable for students who have a 
 basic understanding of drawing and want to work on their skills. Please br
 ing the following materials to class: 20″ x 26″ drawing board with cli
 ps\, 18 “x 24” Strathmore drawing pad \\(other brands are fine as long
  as the paper is drawing quality\\)\, soft willow charcoal\, compressed ch
 arcoal \\(Char-kole brand black\\)\, white plastic eraser\, notebook\, Sta
 edtler drawing pencils 2B and 6B\, Pigma micron pens black \\(one fine-tip
  and one medium-tip\\).Membership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Membershi
 ps and above receive 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase 
 over $40. Materials fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and 
 find community\, connection\, and creativity.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/next-level-drawing/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stitch Together 🧵
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T170000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T190000
UID:260124xFuNFW2RJkO0jsvDnBMEsA
DESCRIPTION:Join us for **Stitch Café**\, a cozy open studio held twice a
  month. Whether you're working on your own project or eager to explore new
  mending techniques like darning and appliqué\, this is the perfect space
  to gather\, share ideas\, and sew together. We provide hand-sewing suppli
 es and materials\, but feel free to bring your own - it's all about commun
 ity\, creativity\, and enjoying the process. By repairing what we already 
 have and re-using materials\, we're not just preserving memories and addin
 g unique touches to our belongings - we’re also reducing waste and contr
 ibuting to a more sustainable lifestyle. We can extend the life of our clo
 thes and fabrics\, and take small but meaningful steps toward caring for t
 he planet.
LOCATION:Art Escape
URL:https://artescapesonoma.jumbula.com/Spring2026/StitchTogether401
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
