END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: Snoopy’s Family
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T100000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T123000
UID:260312KrrmNaUUMkqb7HoLPrMOdQ
DESCRIPTION:Explore the Museum’s newest exhibition\, *Snoopy’s Family
 *\, and learn about animals through hands-on activities. Discover what fam
 ilies in the animal kingdom look like\, explore animal homes\, and try bui
 lding one. Plus\, learn to draw Snoopy and other *Peanuts* animal charac
 ters! Enjoy the optional opportunity to extend the day with ice skating at
  **Snoopy’s Home Ice** from 12:30–2:00 pm. *Recommended for ages 4-
 12.*\n\nThe event features the following guests and interactive activities
 :\n\nRead to a therapy dog with **Paws as Loving Support** (PALS)\n\nMee
 t a senior dog and learn about adopting older dogs with **Brooks Legacy S
 enior Dog Rescue**\n\nUnderstand how you can help animals with **Memorial
  Beach Vet Hospital**\n\nDiscover books about animals with the **Northwes
 t Regional Santa Rosa Library**\n\nCreate stories and comics about animals
  with professional cartoonists\n\nLearn about bears in California with **N
 orth Bay Bear Collaborative**\n\nExplore invertebrates with **Xerces Soci
 ety for Invertebrate Conservation**\n\nInvestigate marine mammals with **
 The Marine Mammal Center**\n\nand more!\n\n**Cost:**\n\n**Youth:** $10.00
  per child by March 25 ($15.00/child after). Includes Museum activities 
 only\, no ice skating.\n\n**Youth + Ice Skating:** $17.00 by March 25 (
 $22.00/child after)\n\n**Chaperones:** Free with paying child (no ice ska
 ting)\n\n**Chaperones + Ice Skating:** $7.00 per person\n\nAll sales are f
 inal\; no refunds available. Registration is required for **all** attend
 ees\, including chaperones. Youth and children cannot attend without an a
 dult chaperone. ***Early registration encouraged\, as this event typicall
 y sells out.***
LOCATION:Charles M. Schulz Museum
URL:https://schulzmuseum.org/homeschool-day-snoopys-family/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Petaluma River Full Moon Paddle
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T184500
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T204500
UID:260306ifRHf8tM7021iTd-7H5kRg
DESCRIPTION:Come play on the river at night.\n\nJoin The Floathouse for a 
 magical evening paddle on the Petaluma River—Petaluma’s Longest Park
 —timed to catch the full moon rising over the wetlands just south of dow
 ntown. As twilight fades\, we’ll head out together in Hobie pedal kayaks
  for a relaxed\, guided glide that turns nighttime into playtime.\n\nThese
  pedal-powered kayaks make the journey smooth and easy\, even if there’s
  a breeze or moving tide. We’ll cruise about a mile and a half downriver
  to the perfect moonrise vantage point\, where calm water\, wide skies\, a
 nd glowing reflections set the scene.\n\nThis is a social\, feel-good outd
 oor experience designed for anyone looking for something a little differen
 t to do after dark—part nature\, part adventure\, part pure vibe.\n\n$60
  per person includes everything: • Hobie pedal kayak • PFD and safety 
 lights • Experienced local guide • A memorable\, moonlit river experie
 nce\n\n✨ Easy. Playful. Peaceful. Spend your evening under the full moon
 —on the water.
LOCATION:The Floathouse Petaluma
URL:https://www.pressdemocrat.com/events/#/details/petaluma-river-full-moo
 n-paddle/17974383/2026-04-01T18
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:S.R. Laws
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T120000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260401T000000
UID:2602273EFu-4Wez0SNrLk0E1-Y2A
DESCRIPTION:S.R. LAWS IS OUT THERE: He approaches songwriting with a passi
 on for songs that we all grew up on. His sound rings a familiar bell in yo
 ur head while still delivering ideas completely unique.  He draws inspirat
 ion from outstanding storytellers like John Hiatt\, Lou Reed\, Steve Earle
 \, Neil Finn and Ron Sexsmith. All of their music and others have carved a
  deep groove. \n\nGrowing up out there in Northern California\, he develop
 ed a unique connection to music early on. His father worked as a trash col
 lector\, and he would spend hours sifting through bags of discarded 45 rec
 ords. Each find felt like stumbling upon hidden treasures. Some records we
 re covered in dirt and grime\, while others were pristine. The thrill of d
 iscovering new sounds was exhilarating\, and he could hardly wait to drop 
 the needle and immerse himself in the music.\n\nHe embarked on a pilgrimag
 e to Texas with just two suitcases and $500 in his bank account. His goal 
 was to dive into the vibrant music scene and learn from fellow songwriters
 . Austin\, known as the "Live Music Capital of the World\," offered countl
 ess opportunities for him to grow as an artist. Open mics and songwriters'
  nights became his training ground\, where he soaked up every moment\, lis
 tening to others share their stories through music.\n\nThese days\, he res
 ides in Sonoma County\, California\, working hard as a touring artist and 
 singer-songwriter for his original rock band\, The Heartsleeves. He invite
 s everyone to join him on this musical journey\, sharing his songs one per
 son at a time in this vast and unpredictable world we live in.\n\n“Scott
  Ray Laws is an unique and really cool songwriter…he digs into materials
 \, tells a story in his songs\, and has a clean baritone vocality that is 
 easy on the ears. We had a chance to meet and hang with Scott back in May 
 ..and I HAD to have him back for a Wednesday evening.” Luigi- Owner-The 
 Listening Room.\n\n“..An ORIGINAL songwriter who knows how to tell a sto
 ry clearly in song” -  Scotty O’Neill - Guitarist/Promoter\n\n“ It w
 as such a treat catching your set last night — really refreshing to hear
  something new and original. Thanks for pulling up a chair and hanging out
  with us — we really enjoyed the conversation and the stories behind you
 r songs.”  -Tripp B. - Sonoma Songwriter\n\n“Expect slow burning passi
 on and vivid music …the kind of energy that turns into “let’s stay f
 or just one more!..”  - Doug- Owner/Wine Maker- Spicy Vines\n\n“...His
  lyrics simply tell first-person stories from his own life. Nothing fancy\
 , he's not writing to impress--he pours himself\, as is\, into each phrase
  and melody.”- Rebecca Roudman- Dirty Cello Radio Hour KRCB Radio 104.9 
 FM\n\n“ It is through forthright lyrics that are personal and earnest\, 
 that he composes lyrical pictures. Taking snapshots from the most common w
 alks of life...”  - David Sampson - Producer Studio Secti West\n\n“..r
 elaxed mid-tempo Americana\, capturing in each song the rhythmic pocket La
 ws is known for creating.” -  Coyote Music Review 2024
LOCATION:Café Frida Gallery
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107812033?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
