DESCRIPTION:Common Ground Book Club Register Here: https://events.sonomali
 brary.o... The first Friday of every month from 10:30 am - 11:30 am 2/06/2
 026- Disability Intimacy: Essays on Love\, Care\, and Desire: Edited by Al
 ice Wong 3/06/2026- The Kiss Quotient by Helen Hoang 04/03/2026- True Biz 
 by Sara Nović 05/01/2026- Second Life: Having a Child in the Digital Age 
 by Amanda Hess Description: Common Ground Society and the Sonoma County Li
 brary are partnering to create a Common Ground Book Club. Meet with others
  to discuss books centering on disability voices. Each month we will read 
 and discuss books about and written by people with disabilities. If you do
 n't have time to read or finish the book you are still welcome to attend. 
 Copies of the books are available through the Sonoma County Regional Libra
 ries. If you are unable to obtain a copy please reach out to Common Ground
  Society at the email below. Registration is encouraged but not required -
  drop ins are welcome. Snacks will be provided. \\*\\*Most books are avail
 able for free in the audio format through Libby\, and/or Hoopla \\(library
  card required\\) If you have any questions please reach out to Heidi Wood
  atsupportcoordinator@commongroundsociety.org Accessibility: The parking l
 ot is paved and has several accessible parking spots. There are ramps lead
 ing into the building from the parking lot. The library is fully accessibl
 e inside. Need translation support at a Common Ground Society meetup? Let 
 us know beforehand and we will make every effort to accommodate your needs
 . Presented By: Common Ground Society and The Sebastopol Regional Library 
 Hosted By: Sebastopol Regional Library Made Possible By: Friends of the Li
 brary commongroundsociety.org
LOCATION:Sebastopol Regional Ligrary
URL:https://www.visitsantarosa.com/events/#jlupcoming-events
