DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T180000
UID:260227V63RGcaqiEyLtvGxlmwidw
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Margo Cilker & Courtney Marie Andrews
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T180000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T000000
UID:260224wHjOmsEHdEC3FCHsRkpwdw
DESCRIPTION:Margo Cilker's sophomore album\, Valley of Heart’s Delight\,
  refers to a place she can't return: California’s Santa Clara Valley\, a
 s it was known before the orchards were paved over and became more famous 
 for Silicon than apricots. In this 11-song follow-up to 2021's critically 
 acclaimed Pohorylle\, family and nature intertwine as guiding motifs\, at 
 once precious and endangered\, beautiful and exhausting. Cilker and Pohory
 lle producer Sera Cahoone brought most of that record's highly-acclaimed c
 rew \\(studio players for The Decemberists\, Band Of Horses\, and Beirut\\
 ) back to the studio with additional contributions from acclaimed Northwes
 t traditionalist Caleb Klauder. Valley of Heart's Delight follows a year b
 usily reaping the fruits of Pohorylle's success\, with festival appearance
 s at Pickathon\, Treefort\, and End Of The Road\, and tours supporting Ame
 rican Aquarium\, Hayes Carll\, Drive-By Truckers\, and Joshua Ray Walker.
LOCATION:Little Saint
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/1036951201?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=2
 87&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to Printmaking Spring Session
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T173000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T193000
UID:2602162DREgzyB70W9mtEwYvpLVA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nTuesdays\, March 31 – April 28\, 2026 5:30 Pm 
 – 7:30 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nBeginning\n\nPrintmaking\n\nAge\\(s\\)\
 n\n16\\+\n\n$195 – Registration Cost $30 – Materials Fee $225 – Tota
 l Registration CostWhat exactly is printmaking? We invite you into our pri
 nt studio to experience a beginner’s journey through this incredible art
  form\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nWhat is printmaking? We invite you into our p
 rint studio to experience a fun beginner’s journey through this incredib
 le art form in five paced weeks. Join Kelly in this unique introduction to
  print through the world of monotype\, relief\, intaglio and stencil scree
 nprinting. This popular multi-session workshop is only taught twice per ye
 ar in the spring and fall seasons. Students will try various techniques in
  this guided\, hands-on class to create a beginning portfolio of prints. L
 earn a basic understanding of the four classic methods within the family o
 f printmaking and gain access to our member’s print studio to continue w
 orking on your own projects. This class is perfect for absolute beginners 
 or even experienced artists who may need a refresher course in printmaking
 . \n\nMonotype – Create a single print on a flat matrix using ink and a
  variety of marks and  textures\n\nRelief – Carve\, ink and block print
  using a mini speedy carve block and a linocut tool\n\nIntaglio – Draw\,
  scratch and ink onto a surface to roll out a creative print using a small
  press\n\nStencil – Pull a silkscreen and learn to transfer a flat stenc
 il to make a colorful printed impression\n\nNo prior printmaking experienc
 e is necessary. This class requires hand dexterity to maneuver carving too
 ls and studio equipment. Students must feel comfortable handling machinery
 .\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above recei
 ve 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $40. Material
 s fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find community\, c
 onnection\, and creativity.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/introduction-to-printmaking
 -spring-session/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Adult Gymnastics Class
DTSTART;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T183000
DTEND;TZID=PDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260407T200000
UID:260214PoFca-e07UeWAS4w-Sp49w
DESCRIPTION:**We’re offering Adult Gymnastics Classes for the 18+ crowd!
 **\n\n**Adult Gymnastics classes occur every Tuesday 5:00 PM to 6:30 PM &
  Friday from 6:30 PM to 8:00 PM.**\n\n**$20 per person\, OR pay for a wh
 ole 8-week session in advance through our site. You can attend on Tuesday\
 , Friday\, or both!**\n\n**Please bring the class fee in cash at the time 
 of arrival. This can be a DROP IN\, so there is no need to sign up online 
 before coming!**\n\nIf you’ve ever wanted to try out gymnastics or get b
 ack into it in adulthood\, now is your chance! During our adult classes\, 
 open to all genders\, our coaches will move at the pace of each student\, 
 helping them achieve goals they set for themselves. **No experience is ne
 cessary** to be involved in this class\, so this is a great opportunity t
 o learn the basics and get some exercise\, no matter what age you are! Try
  out our trampoline\, bars\, beam\, and other gym equipment in a safe and 
 supportive environment. You can build strength and increase your range of 
 motion while having fun like you’re a kid again.\n\nAsk our coaches what
  you can work on between classes\, and they’ll help personalize your tra
 ining!\n\nPlease wear something comfortable and keep long hair tied back. 
 Skirts and restrictive clothing are not recommended. You must remove your 
 shoes before going onto the mat or using equipment. Please let us know if 
 you have any physical limitations or health conditions that may interfere 
 with doing certain motions. We recommend bringing a water bottle.\n\nYou c
 an email us for more info or join our mailing list at: info@sonomagymnast
 icsacademy.com
LOCATION:Sonoma Gymnastics Academy
URL:https://sonomagymnasticsacademy.com/home/adult-gymnastics-night/
X-SOURCE:Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
